1
00:00:22,764 --> 00:00:25,392
There he is!
Over there! Don't let him get away!

2
00:00:42,242 --> 00:00:44,202
How dare he run into
the Holy Grounds!

3
00:00:46,079 --> 00:00:47,622
This area is off-limits.

4
00:00:48,123 --> 00:00:49,123
Over there!

5
00:00:50,459 --> 00:00:52,335
I'm not going to make it like this.

6
00:00:59,301 --> 00:01:00,301
This is...

7
00:01:00,343 --> 00:01:01,343
Stop there!

8
00:01:01,678 --> 00:01:02,678
Give it up!

9
00:01:02,929 --> 00:01:05,932
<i>Vitolau Lahike Lisoyora Chidai!</i>

10
00:01:09,811 --> 00:01:11,480
No! You mustn't go through there!

11
00:02:23,093 --> 00:02:24,427
<i>Hello, everyone.</i>

12
00:02:25,428 --> 00:02:28,431
<i>It's almost the birthday of my
father Bartra, the King of Liones.</i>

13
00:02:28,557 --> 00:02:29,891
<i>Just three days left.</i>

14
00:02:30,767 --> 00:02:33,687
<i>A celebration calls for
delicious cooking,</i>

15
00:02:33,895 --> 00:02:35,980
<i>which is why we've come
to the borderlands,</i>

16
00:02:35,981 --> 00:02:37,899
<i>in search of wonderful ingredients.</i>

17
00:02:38,859 --> 00:02:42,904
<i>Oh, if only all of our trips
were so peaceful.</i>

18
00:03:14,603 --> 00:03:16,813
You're all back so quick!

19
00:03:17,439 --> 00:03:18,857
Oh, where's the captain?

20
00:03:19,524 --> 00:03:22,360
Hm, the air smells good here.

21
00:03:23,820 --> 00:03:24,820
Meliodas!

22
00:03:25,530 --> 00:03:27,532
Great reaction, Elizabeth!

23
00:03:32,120 --> 00:03:34,414
What the heck are you
doing, you perv!

24
00:03:34,789 --> 00:03:39,210
Didn't the captain say he was going
to go catch a flying fish?

25
00:03:39,961 --> 00:03:40,962
A sky fish!

26
00:03:41,421 --> 00:03:43,381
Really? I wanna see!

27
00:03:43,590 --> 00:03:45,508
Where's this sky fish?

28
00:03:45,717 --> 00:03:47,093
Yeah, well...

29
00:03:47,719 --> 00:03:50,180
I can't find it anywhere.

30
00:03:50,847 --> 00:03:52,557
You won't find it there!

31
00:03:53,266 --> 00:03:54,266
Sky fish.

32
00:03:55,101 --> 00:03:59,189
A creature only mentioned
in legends. A fish with wings.

33
00:03:59,481 --> 00:04:03,693
We came because the captain
said we'd find them here.

34
00:04:03,818 --> 00:04:07,906
Those rumors are apparently from
a legend from 1,000 years ago.

35
00:04:08,657 --> 00:04:10,825
The captain just
wanted to slack off.

36
00:04:11,409 --> 00:04:12,869
That's just like him.

37
00:04:13,203 --> 00:04:16,539
More importantly, Captain,
let's hurry and get to it.

38
00:04:16,665 --> 00:04:18,166
Right, time to train.

39
00:04:18,667 --> 00:04:19,667
Training?

40
00:04:25,924 --> 00:04:30,637
Hope you're ready for this, Bartra! I'm
going to treat you to my best dishes!

41
00:04:33,056 --> 00:04:36,935
You, who can only make food scraps?
You're going to learn to cook?

42
00:04:38,144 --> 00:04:40,522
Please teach me, Master Ban!

43
00:04:41,564 --> 00:04:43,900
You know what's what, Captain.

44
00:04:44,275 --> 00:04:47,612
- Okay, we'll start with an apple pie.
- Great!

45
00:04:49,280 --> 00:04:51,032
You can be my sous chef, Elizabeth!

46
00:04:53,493 --> 00:04:54,995
Ta-da!

47
00:04:55,120 --> 00:04:56,621
You're Gowther!

48
00:04:57,038 --> 00:04:59,791
You stole our uniform again!

49
00:04:59,958 --> 00:05:02,127
You'd better pay for that.

50
00:05:02,627 --> 00:05:04,254
First, we peel the skin.

51
00:05:07,007 --> 00:05:09,259
Peel it, not destroy it!

52
00:05:09,926 --> 00:05:11,511
No, don't pick it up!

53
00:05:12,095 --> 00:05:13,221
Flour...

54
00:05:13,388 --> 00:05:14,888
And a pinch of salt!

55
00:05:14,889 --> 00:05:16,224
That's not a pinch!

56
00:05:16,808 --> 00:05:17,934
Then we stir...

57
00:05:18,143 --> 00:05:20,270
You're supposed to add water first!

58
00:05:20,729 --> 00:05:22,063
Then we stretch the dough.

59
00:05:22,188 --> 00:05:23,398
It's not a pizza, Captain!

60
00:05:24,149 --> 00:05:25,275
Then we wrap the apples.

61
00:05:25,400 --> 00:05:27,110
You haven't cut them yet!

62
00:05:27,569 --> 00:05:28,820
Now, let's bake!

63
00:05:29,029 --> 00:05:31,072
- Good grief...
- That's the end of that.

64
00:05:32,449 --> 00:05:34,451
What's going on here?

65
00:05:38,121 --> 00:05:39,539
It looks delicious!

66
00:05:39,748 --> 00:05:40,874
Impossible.

67
00:05:42,000 --> 00:05:43,418
It's visually perfect.

68
00:05:43,543 --> 00:05:45,502
I made sure to focus on that.

69
00:05:45,503 --> 00:05:46,963
You should focus on all of it.

70
00:05:47,672 --> 00:05:49,549
And now, it's taste test time!

71
00:05:50,133 --> 00:05:51,341
How about it, King?

72
00:05:51,342 --> 00:05:52,342
Huh?

73
00:05:52,552 --> 00:05:55,637
Um... I haven't been feeling well
all morning.

74
00:05:55,638 --> 00:05:56,555
Diane?

75
00:05:56,556 --> 00:05:59,017
Uh... I just ate.

76
00:05:59,350 --> 00:06:00,350
Master Ban?

77
00:06:00,351 --> 00:06:01,351
I'm gonna kill you.

78
00:06:02,103 --> 00:06:04,272
Nope, you've got no sense of taste!

79
00:06:04,981 --> 00:06:06,107
How about you, Merlin?

80
00:06:07,108 --> 00:06:09,194
You're telling me to eat that thing?

81
00:06:09,569 --> 00:06:10,695
I shall eat it.

82
00:06:12,155 --> 00:06:16,618
It is part of my duties
to protect Merlin.

83
00:06:33,885 --> 00:06:35,220
What's happening?

84
00:06:42,310 --> 00:06:45,313
There's a spring
just past the brush.

85
00:06:45,438 --> 00:06:46,815
Why don't you head there?

86
00:06:47,315 --> 00:06:49,317
How did I get caught up in this?

87
00:06:50,652 --> 00:06:52,987
Man, that was horrible.

88
00:06:53,113 --> 00:06:54,363
Don't be stupid!

89
00:06:54,364 --> 00:06:57,492
Escanor's the one who
got the worst of it.

90
00:06:57,742 --> 00:06:59,661
Oh, that must be the spring!

91
00:07:00,036 --> 00:07:02,330
Let's hurry up and wash this off.

92
00:07:02,580 --> 00:07:05,250
Why don't you just
eat it like usual?

93
00:07:06,042 --> 00:07:08,670
I can't eat the stuff
that's on my butt!

94
00:07:10,547 --> 00:07:11,923
Hm? What's that?

95
00:07:13,299 --> 00:07:15,093
Oh, wow!

96
00:07:15,385 --> 00:07:17,636
Something's glowing in the spring!

97
00:07:17,637 --> 00:07:19,139
What's going on?

98
00:07:30,400 --> 00:07:31,567
Did you see that, Hawk?

99
00:07:31,568 --> 00:07:33,319
There were fish flying in the sky!

100
00:07:33,444 --> 00:07:34,863
Could it be?

101
00:07:35,280 --> 00:07:36,531
Sky fish!

102
00:07:37,031 --> 00:07:39,075
All right! Let's go catch them!

103
00:07:39,200 --> 00:07:42,787
Yeah, I'll show you
my graceful pig-paddle!

104
00:08:12,734 --> 00:08:13,985
What is this place?

105
00:08:24,662 --> 00:08:25,955
I can't believe it!

106
00:08:26,998 --> 00:08:28,124
A vast land!

107
00:08:31,211 --> 00:08:33,213
The Great Oshiro must be here.

108
00:08:33,338 --> 00:08:34,505
Hey!

109
00:08:35,798 --> 00:08:37,675
Hurry up and come back!

110
00:08:40,136 --> 00:08:41,512
Wait, where are you going?

111
00:08:42,180 --> 00:08:45,266
I can't believe they'd chase me
here. Why won't they understand?

112
00:08:45,683 --> 00:08:47,101
Giving up already?

113
00:08:47,310 --> 00:08:50,230
You're the one who said
you're going to train, Captain.

114
00:08:50,855 --> 00:08:52,565
Cap... tain?

115
00:08:57,612 --> 00:09:00,073
Whoa, you're flying without wings!

116
00:09:00,323 --> 00:09:03,785
S-So what if I don't have wings?
What's it to you, Captain?

117
00:09:03,993 --> 00:09:04,993
Who cares!

118
00:09:05,328 --> 00:09:06,329
He's not after me?

119
00:09:06,996 --> 00:09:08,539
Could it be... the Demon Clan?

120
00:09:08,957 --> 00:09:09,957
Huh?

121
00:09:18,508 --> 00:09:20,260
What's all the ruckus?

122
00:09:22,303 --> 00:09:25,014
Oh, where'd you get that
outfit, Captain?

123
00:09:25,431 --> 00:09:26,599
It's so cute!

124
00:09:27,976 --> 00:09:29,519
Monster!

125
00:09:33,982 --> 00:09:37,151
Captain,
are we continuing the train...

126
00:09:38,152 --> 00:09:43,031
How could he?
The captain called me a monster!

127
00:09:43,032 --> 00:09:44,450
Don't let it bother you, Diane.

128
00:09:47,453 --> 00:09:51,582
Coming back on your
knees is a good start.

129
00:09:51,708 --> 00:09:53,376
What's going on here?

130
00:09:53,793 --> 00:09:56,337
Huh, how should I know?

131
00:10:03,845 --> 00:10:05,138
What's up with these guys?

132
00:10:05,763 --> 00:10:10,518
Hair color, height, frame. All of
it matches that of the captain.

133
00:10:10,643 --> 00:10:15,773
But there is striking difference in
voice, power, and the way he runs.

134
00:10:15,940 --> 00:10:17,191
You're right.

135
00:10:17,775 --> 00:10:22,655
Normally, there'd be no way we could
catch up so easily.

136
00:10:24,532 --> 00:10:26,826
Right, Captain?

137
00:10:27,201 --> 00:10:28,201
Huh?

138
00:10:32,165 --> 00:10:33,165
Wha...

139
00:10:34,334 --> 00:10:35,209
No way.

140
00:10:35,335 --> 00:10:36,377
The captain...

141
00:10:38,463 --> 00:10:41,174
grew wings?

142
00:10:43,217 --> 00:10:44,344
Hey, wait!

143
00:10:52,268 --> 00:10:54,270
I hope that wasn't too rough.

144
00:11:01,986 --> 00:11:03,654
Now, let's see...

145
00:11:04,447 --> 00:11:07,075
Where am I?

146
00:11:08,368 --> 00:11:10,370
It's no use. We can't go back.

147
00:11:11,454 --> 00:11:14,832
We went into the spring
in the forest, right?

148
00:11:18,044 --> 00:11:19,337
But that aside...

149
00:11:23,674 --> 00:11:25,051
- I'm hungry!
- I'm hungry!

150
00:11:25,468 --> 00:11:26,468
This way.

151
00:11:27,470 --> 00:11:29,931
Did he really enter
the forbidden spring?

152
00:11:30,807 --> 00:11:31,641
There he is!

153
00:11:31,766 --> 00:11:32,766
He came back?

154
00:11:33,476 --> 00:11:35,227
There's a strange creature with him.

155
00:11:35,228 --> 00:11:38,231
- Hey, who are those guys?
- Don't ask me.

156
00:11:41,901 --> 00:11:43,069
Master Zoria.

157
00:11:44,487 --> 00:11:46,239
Why, Solaad?

158
00:11:46,864 --> 00:11:48,741
Huh? Solaad?

159
00:11:50,410 --> 00:11:51,452
Take him.

160
00:11:51,619 --> 00:11:52,619
Yes, sir!

161
00:11:54,247 --> 00:11:55,247
Come!

162
00:11:55,373 --> 00:11:56,373
Thanks.

163
00:11:56,416 --> 00:11:59,836
Back off, you pigs!

164
00:12:00,002 --> 00:12:01,003
P-Pigs?

165
00:12:01,295 --> 00:12:04,465
Master Zoria, what should we do
with this creature?

166
00:12:04,715 --> 00:12:06,676
Leave that thing be.

167
00:12:06,843 --> 00:12:09,303
What? I'm not a<i> thing!</i>

168
00:12:17,103 --> 00:12:23,317
These statues are weird looking.
By the way, where are we?

169
00:12:31,576 --> 00:12:32,910
What are you doing?

170
00:12:42,795 --> 00:12:45,339
Wow, what an amazing view!

171
00:12:48,551 --> 00:12:49,551
Hey, look.

172
00:13:01,355 --> 00:13:03,065
What are those?

173
00:13:06,110 --> 00:13:07,528
Whoa!

174
00:13:12,658 --> 00:13:14,076
Sky fish!

175
00:13:26,047 --> 00:13:27,381
Wow!

176
00:13:35,431 --> 00:13:36,599
This must be...

177
00:13:38,684 --> 00:13:40,019
Could it be?

178
00:13:42,813 --> 00:13:46,943
We're above the sky!

179
00:14:21,519 --> 00:14:24,689
Oh, you're awake. I'm so glad.

180
00:14:26,524 --> 00:14:28,651
Ellatte? Why are you here, Elle?

181
00:14:29,151 --> 00:14:30,151
Ellatte?

182
00:14:30,528 --> 00:14:32,363
And why are you dressed like that?

183
00:14:33,573 --> 00:14:36,534
Hey, what'd you do with the captain?

184
00:14:37,368 --> 00:14:38,368
Damn it!

185
00:14:42,540 --> 00:14:46,502
Elle, hurry, run!
I'll hold off the Demon Clan!

186
00:14:46,752 --> 00:14:49,422
I think you may have the wrong idea.

187
00:14:50,548 --> 00:14:52,049
All of us here,

188
00:14:52,216 --> 00:14:55,678
we may come from different clans, but
none of us are from the Demon Clan.

189
00:14:56,178 --> 00:14:57,178
He's human.

190
00:14:57,346 --> 00:14:58,347
He's a former human.

191
00:14:59,056 --> 00:15:01,434
And, well, I'm something like that.

192
00:15:01,976 --> 00:15:04,103
He's a doll,
and he's from the Fairy Clan.

193
00:15:04,937 --> 00:15:06,606
She's from the Giant Clan.

194
00:15:07,064 --> 00:15:08,149
That can't be!

195
00:15:08,608 --> 00:15:12,445
I thought that on Earth, the humans,
the Fairy Clan, and Giant Clan...

196
00:15:13,738 --> 00:15:16,699
were all wiped out by the Demon Clan
during the ancient war.

197
00:15:18,117 --> 00:15:21,537
Were the legends passed down to us
mistaken then?

198
00:15:23,998 --> 00:15:25,041
Then you...

199
00:15:25,207 --> 00:15:26,584
I'm Elizabeth.

200
00:15:27,084 --> 00:15:28,794
A waitress at this pub.

201
00:15:30,713 --> 00:15:34,634
- Oh, um, I'm a Celest...
- A Celestial. Solaad.

202
00:15:35,468 --> 00:15:36,969
How do you know my name?

203
00:15:37,094 --> 00:15:39,764
I peeked in your memories
while you were asleep.

204
00:15:41,057 --> 00:15:43,517
What is the "Time of Ruin"?

205
00:15:50,608 --> 00:15:53,401
Are they preparing for a festival?

206
00:15:53,402 --> 00:15:55,404
Maybe it's a festival to eat you.

207
00:15:56,113 --> 00:15:58,573
Don't let them put
roast pig on the menu!

208
00:15:58,574 --> 00:16:02,035
- Maybe they can just lick my feet.
- Coward.

209
00:16:02,036 --> 00:16:03,995
What was he thinking?

210
00:16:03,996 --> 00:16:05,998
To think he's to be our next
Head Warrior...

211
00:16:08,501 --> 00:16:10,628
This is quite the welcome.

212
00:16:17,718 --> 00:16:20,805
What's that? Looks like a fat pig.

213
00:16:20,971 --> 00:16:23,264
So, it's just like you?

214
00:16:23,265 --> 00:16:25,267
Don't be ridiculous!
I'm much slimmer.

215
00:16:25,393 --> 00:16:27,937
What are you going on about?

216
00:16:28,562 --> 00:16:29,896
Now see here, Solaad.

217
00:16:29,897 --> 00:16:32,858
You've committed a grave crime
by breaking the law.

218
00:16:33,567 --> 00:16:34,985
The statue talked!

219
00:16:35,528 --> 00:16:36,737
Look below!

220
00:16:38,030 --> 00:16:41,283
You've got some nerve joking around
under these circumstances.

221
00:16:42,493 --> 00:16:43,493
She's tiny.

222
00:16:43,828 --> 00:16:47,790
Although you are the successor
to the Winged Sword,

223
00:16:47,957 --> 00:16:50,918
I know too well how much
you hated your training.

224
00:16:51,836 --> 00:16:53,337
But Solaad...

225
00:16:54,630 --> 00:16:57,257
In order to protect our people
from the Demon Clan,

226
00:16:57,258 --> 00:17:01,220
this Winged Sword has been passed down
for generations and used to fight!

227
00:17:02,096 --> 00:17:05,057
That is the law for us Celestials.

228
00:17:05,391 --> 00:17:06,726
Celestials?

229
00:17:07,101 --> 00:17:10,646
Hey, are you mistaking me
for someone else, Granny?

230
00:17:11,105 --> 00:17:12,189
Gran...

231
00:17:13,065 --> 00:17:15,233
How dare you address Mistress
Vaness in that manner!

232
00:17:15,234 --> 00:17:17,236
What were you thinking, Solaad?

233
00:17:17,987 --> 00:17:20,239
What was I thinking?

234
00:17:20,614 --> 00:17:21,824
Solaad is back?

235
00:17:25,578 --> 00:17:26,787
Elizabeth?

236
00:17:27,580 --> 00:17:29,832
Meliodas, it's Elizabeth!

237
00:17:30,166 --> 00:17:31,124
Let me go!

238
00:17:31,125 --> 00:17:32,418
She's totally different.

239
00:17:32,543 --> 00:17:33,543
Huh, really?

240
00:17:34,420 --> 00:17:36,005
Now that you mention it,

241
00:17:36,255 --> 00:17:38,758
her expression is
harsh for Elizabeth.

242
00:17:39,341 --> 00:17:42,970
But they look so alike.
Even her hair is the same color.

243
00:17:43,095 --> 00:17:45,389
Oh, and on her back, there's...

244
00:17:46,474 --> 00:17:47,640
w-wings?

245
00:17:47,641 --> 00:17:48,976
Miss Ellatte!

246
00:17:55,524 --> 00:17:56,524
Solaad!

247
00:17:59,820 --> 00:18:01,655
Why did you do this?

248
00:18:02,782 --> 00:18:03,782
Huh?

249
00:18:08,162 --> 00:18:10,414
He has no... wings!

250
00:18:11,707 --> 00:18:12,707
His wings...

251
00:18:13,292 --> 00:18:15,376
Solaad's wings have disappeared!

252
00:18:15,377 --> 00:18:16,420
Mistress Vaness.

253
00:18:17,046 --> 00:18:19,173
That's... impossible!

254
00:18:19,965 --> 00:18:22,092
He's lost his wings?

255
00:18:22,468 --> 00:18:26,180
Our pride...
Have you sunk so low?

256
00:18:26,305 --> 00:18:27,723
So, I'm telling you...

257
00:18:28,224 --> 00:18:31,393
He ran from the
Succession Ceremony...

258
00:18:31,685 --> 00:18:35,314
and now he's returned without
the wings of our people!

259
00:18:35,689 --> 00:18:38,442
Any further discussion
is a waste of time!

260
00:18:39,443 --> 00:18:43,030
You can sit in a cell and
reflect upon your actions!

261
00:18:43,405 --> 00:18:44,865
Please wait!

262
00:18:45,241 --> 00:18:46,492
That's fine with me.

263
00:18:46,700 --> 00:18:47,700
Solaad!

264
00:18:47,743 --> 00:18:50,871
Just make sure to prepare
some food and sake.

265
00:18:52,456 --> 00:18:54,291
I've lost all faith in you!

266
00:18:55,501 --> 00:18:57,962
You are no longer my son.

267
00:19:00,589 --> 00:19:01,589
Son?

268
00:19:03,175 --> 00:19:05,177
Well, I'm not your son, so...

269
00:19:09,348 --> 00:19:10,766
Sorry, Meliodas.

270
00:19:11,141 --> 00:19:13,310
We can't afford for
me to be captured too.

271
00:19:13,894 --> 00:19:15,896
Until I come rescue you,

272
00:19:16,063 --> 00:19:18,440
you can eat scraps in prison
while you wait.

273
00:19:29,451 --> 00:19:34,247
You look just like the captain, but
your personality is totally different.

274
00:19:34,248 --> 00:19:36,834
You've got the rudeness in common
with him too.

275
00:19:37,001 --> 00:19:38,752
Just let it go, King.

276
00:19:39,128 --> 00:19:40,713
I'm sorry about earlier.

277
00:19:41,380 --> 00:19:44,008
I'd never seen a Giant before.

278
00:19:44,800 --> 00:19:47,261
I'm... really sorry.

279
00:19:49,388 --> 00:19:52,182
So, the captain went into the spring

280
00:19:52,349 --> 00:19:54,810
and ended up in the Sky Temple
or whatever you call it?

281
00:19:55,102 --> 00:19:58,939
That must mean Hawk
is with him as well.

282
00:19:59,273 --> 00:20:01,609
He probably jumped
in without thinking.

283
00:20:01,775 --> 00:20:03,485
Sounds like our captain.

284
00:20:03,777 --> 00:20:04,777
So...

285
00:20:05,029 --> 00:20:06,404
You freaked at the idea

286
00:20:06,405 --> 00:20:09,199
of the Demon Clan
being resurrected and ran?

287
00:20:09,491 --> 00:20:11,118
I didn't run!

288
00:20:11,619 --> 00:20:14,955
The seal that was used to trap
the Demon Clan 3,000 years ago

289
00:20:15,289 --> 00:20:16,957
is about to vanish.

290
00:20:17,625 --> 00:20:19,960
At this rate, the Celestials
will be wiped out.

291
00:20:20,502 --> 00:20:22,963
So, that's what's meant
by the "Time of Ruin."

292
00:20:23,631 --> 00:20:27,051
According to the legend, we need
the Great Oshiro.

293
00:20:28,469 --> 00:20:30,471
No one will believe me, but...

294
00:20:31,263 --> 00:20:32,890
I have to do something.

295
00:20:33,515 --> 00:20:36,477
The Great Oshiro? What's that?

296
00:20:36,769 --> 00:20:39,146
The Time of Ruin and
the Great Oshiro...

297
00:20:40,022 --> 00:20:41,482
It's quite fascinating.

298
00:20:42,566 --> 00:20:44,360
Tell us more.

299
00:20:46,445 --> 00:20:47,445
Okay.

300
00:20:52,952 --> 00:20:55,496
These food scraps are pretty good!

301
00:20:57,706 --> 00:21:01,877
It can use the human language?
What a fantastical creature.

302
00:21:02,544 --> 00:21:05,464
Where in the world
did you come from?

303
00:21:07,925 --> 00:21:11,095
You're so smooth and round!

304
00:21:13,597 --> 00:21:16,433
Stop that, Granny, I can't eat!

305
00:21:16,725 --> 00:21:18,727
What's that, Granny?

306
00:21:20,020 --> 00:21:21,146
Oh, that?

307
00:21:21,772 --> 00:21:22,772
That's...

308
00:21:27,277 --> 00:21:29,530
the legend of the Great Oshiro.

309
00:21:30,072 --> 00:21:31,407
The Great Oshiro?

310
00:21:31,865 --> 00:21:35,285
Three thousand years ago,
here in the Sky Temple,

311
00:21:35,411 --> 00:21:39,164
there was a great war
amongst five clans.

312
00:21:40,290 --> 00:21:44,335
It's said that the evil Demon Clan
and Goddess Clan-led armies

313
00:21:44,336 --> 00:21:49,925
of the Fairy, Giant, and Human clans
fought a terrible battle.

314
00:21:50,801 --> 00:21:55,930
One of the Goddess Clan's companies
was surrounded by giant Demons

315
00:21:55,931 --> 00:21:58,017
and was in danger of annihilation.

316
00:21:58,684 --> 00:22:02,229
It was the Great
Oshiro that saved them.

317
00:22:04,106 --> 00:22:07,568
Large and grand in form,

318
00:22:07,818 --> 00:22:11,697
it's been said that he shone
with a white light.

319
00:22:14,033 --> 00:22:17,619
The Great Oshiro sealed away
the Demon Clan on Craggy Peak.

320
00:22:18,328 --> 00:22:22,623
And Goddess Clan has been handing down
the Winged Sword through the generations

321
00:22:22,624 --> 00:22:24,168
to defeat the Demon Clan.

322
00:22:24,710 --> 00:22:28,672
We Celestials are descendants
of the Goddess Clan.

323
00:22:29,757 --> 00:22:34,178
So, you're here to search
for this legendary Great Oshiro?

324
00:22:34,678 --> 00:22:35,678
Yeah.

325
00:22:36,055 --> 00:22:40,100
If the legends are right, the Great
Oshiro should be here on Earth.

326
00:22:41,268 --> 00:22:43,479
But no one will believe me.

327
00:22:44,563 --> 00:22:47,649
And it's forbidden to go to Earth
to begin with.

328
00:22:48,317 --> 00:22:49,943
The Great Oshiro, huh?

329
00:22:50,402 --> 00:22:51,945
Have you heard of him, Gowther?

330
00:22:52,488 --> 00:22:53,488
No.

331
00:22:54,782 --> 00:22:57,367
Hey, let's help him look.

332
00:22:58,535 --> 00:23:02,331
Even if we wanted to,
there are no leads. What can we do?

333
00:23:02,790 --> 00:23:08,837
I wonder how the captain and Hawk
are doing? I'm worried about them.

334
00:23:08,962 --> 00:23:10,839
Maybe they're on a vacation.

335
00:23:11,006 --> 00:23:13,258
Ooh, I want to go too!

336
00:23:13,759 --> 00:23:17,054
H-Huh? If Diane's going, I am too.

337
00:23:17,429 --> 00:23:20,808
We'll drag him back and make him
continue the training.

338
00:23:21,308 --> 00:23:23,184
We can get there through the spring?

339
00:23:23,185 --> 00:23:26,772
Yes. I'm interested in
this "Sky Temple" as well.

340
00:23:27,523 --> 00:23:30,359
But, what about the Great Oshiro?

341
00:23:37,741 --> 00:23:41,703
Thank you, everyone.
But I'll be fine on my own.

342
00:23:42,287 --> 00:23:43,288
I'll be going, then!

343
00:23:43,413 --> 00:23:45,040
Wait, Solaad!

344
00:23:46,959 --> 00:23:49,628
Hm. He's gone.

345
00:23:55,884 --> 00:23:57,719
<i>I can't depend on someone else.</i>

346
00:23:58,220 --> 00:24:01,723
<i>I promised myself I'll find
the Great Oshiro here on my own.</i>

347
00:24:02,349 --> 00:24:03,349
<i>But...</i>

348
00:24:03,809 --> 00:24:06,436
<i>these lands are so vast and
I have no leads.</i>

349
00:24:06,645 --> 00:24:08,147
<i>Where do I start looking?</i>

350
00:24:11,483 --> 00:24:12,483
<i>What's that?</i>

351
00:24:23,871 --> 00:24:25,789
You're mine now.

352
00:24:28,167 --> 00:24:29,167
Who are you?

353
00:24:34,715 --> 00:24:38,510
Celestials must all be sacrificed!

354
00:24:39,428 --> 00:24:41,722
For the Time of Ruin.

355
00:24:42,681 --> 00:24:45,184
It can't be! The Demon Clan?

356
00:24:45,350 --> 00:24:46,977
What the hell are you doing?

357
00:24:49,188 --> 00:24:50,731
What happened, Solaad?

358
00:24:50,856 --> 00:24:53,316
The Demon Clan came
through the spring!

359
00:24:53,317 --> 00:24:55,194
You can leave this to us!

360
00:24:56,111 --> 00:24:58,739
I'll turn you into sacrifices too!

361
00:25:02,659 --> 00:25:03,702
These guys...

362
00:25:03,994 --> 00:25:06,496
You're Gara from the
Six Knights of Black.

363
00:25:07,039 --> 00:25:08,457
How do you know that?

364
00:25:10,167 --> 00:25:11,627
Who are you guys?

365
00:25:13,212 --> 00:25:14,296
We...

366
00:25:15,631 --> 00:25:17,633
are the Seven Deadly Sins.

367
00:25:19,384 --> 00:25:21,970
A nuisance either way!

368
00:25:23,931 --> 00:25:26,767
So, here's a gift for you all!

369
00:25:40,072 --> 00:25:41,072
The spring!

370
00:25:44,451 --> 00:25:48,038
Now you won't be able to go
to the Sky Temple.

371
00:25:48,580 --> 00:25:52,876
Soon, the Six Knights of Black
will annihilate the Celestials.

372
00:25:54,253 --> 00:25:55,796
I won't let you get in the wa...

373
00:26:00,759 --> 00:26:02,427
That was just a puppet.

374
00:26:03,011 --> 00:26:04,763
Her real body is elsewhere.

375
00:26:05,305 --> 00:26:06,348
I didn't think...

376
00:26:07,057 --> 00:26:10,018
the Demon Clan
would be resurrected so soon.

377
00:26:11,019 --> 00:26:13,814
Hey, what was that about?

378
00:26:16,858 --> 00:26:18,443
The Six Knights of Black.

379
00:26:19,486 --> 00:26:23,448
Demons that went on a rampage
during the war 3,000 years ago.

380
00:26:25,325 --> 00:26:27,243
It's said that they were so violent,

381
00:26:27,244 --> 00:26:30,163
even the Ten Commandments struggled
with them.

382
00:26:33,458 --> 00:26:34,835
It's all over.

383
00:26:35,919 --> 00:26:38,255
I haven't even found
the Great Oshiro.

384
00:26:39,047 --> 00:26:42,092
We can't just leave this be.

385
00:26:42,759 --> 00:26:44,761
If we can't use the spring,

386
00:26:45,220 --> 00:26:47,764
we've no choice but
to go there directly.

387
00:26:54,021 --> 00:26:55,355
Let's go, King!

388
00:26:55,480 --> 00:26:57,858
Huh? Wait for me, Diane!

389
00:26:58,608 --> 00:26:59,608
Let's go.

390
00:27:05,365 --> 00:27:07,909
- You're coming too.
- But...

391
00:27:08,410 --> 00:27:10,871
The Demon Clan has already been
resurrected, right?

392
00:27:19,046 --> 00:27:22,758
And we're off to the mystical land -
the Sky Temple!

393
00:27:38,857 --> 00:27:40,442
Hey, anyone there?

394
00:27:43,028 --> 00:27:44,488
Nope, no one here.

395
00:27:48,700 --> 00:27:50,409
Now, what to do?

396
00:27:50,410 --> 00:27:53,413
I need to figure out which direction
the pub's in.

397
00:27:54,623 --> 00:27:57,000
Guess I'll look for
that damn pig first.

398
00:28:01,922 --> 00:28:03,048
Hey, Granny.

399
00:28:03,173 --> 00:28:06,468
I came from Earth.
Is there a way to get back?

400
00:28:08,553 --> 00:28:09,553
Like I said...

401
00:28:10,514 --> 00:28:15,102
Earth was conquered
by the Demon Clan ages ago.

402
00:28:15,519 --> 00:28:17,687
And I'm telling you it wasn't.

403
00:28:17,979 --> 00:28:20,982
You say the strangest things.

404
00:28:21,858 --> 00:28:23,402
Not again!

405
00:28:27,989 --> 00:28:29,699
What's your problem?

406
00:28:29,825 --> 00:28:30,909
I'm sorry.

407
00:28:34,621 --> 00:28:36,623
- What?
- You look like...

408
00:28:37,165 --> 00:28:38,291
Could it be?

409
00:28:39,167 --> 00:28:40,710
Yes, there's no mistake!

410
00:28:41,253 --> 00:28:42,253
Huh?

411
00:28:56,726 --> 00:28:58,687
This is a Year of Doom.

412
00:28:58,854 --> 00:29:01,940
We don't know how many
of the Demon Clan will appear.

413
00:29:02,524 --> 00:29:06,153
It is our duty as Celestials
to stop them.

414
00:29:06,695 --> 00:29:08,822
We must not let our guard down!

415
00:29:08,947 --> 00:29:10,824
Yes, sir!

416
00:29:18,874 --> 00:29:22,002
Man, the view is amazing.

417
00:29:24,588 --> 00:29:27,048
I wish I could show Elizabeth.

418
00:29:36,266 --> 00:29:37,100
Hey!

419
00:29:37,225 --> 00:29:38,768
S-Solaad!

420
00:29:42,230 --> 00:29:44,900
How did you get out of the prison?

421
00:29:45,108 --> 00:29:48,236
- You keep mistaking me...
- You had me worried!

422
00:29:49,154 --> 00:29:51,614
Why'd you duck? Let me hit you!

423
00:29:51,615 --> 00:29:54,534
I'm not obligated to let
a stranger hit me.

424
00:29:55,243 --> 00:29:56,578
Sorry to have to tell you,

425
00:29:57,162 --> 00:29:59,706
but I'm not Solaad.

426
00:30:02,459 --> 00:30:03,543
What do you mean?

427
00:30:04,503 --> 00:30:05,503
There he is!

428
00:30:07,172 --> 00:30:08,172
Master Zoria.

429
00:30:13,803 --> 00:30:14,803
You!

430
00:30:14,888 --> 00:30:19,226
Not only have you broken the law, you
can't even sit in prison to reflect.

431
00:30:20,477 --> 00:30:21,770
I can't forgive this.

432
00:30:22,062 --> 00:30:24,981
I'm not going to hold back
just because you're my son!

433
00:30:26,775 --> 00:30:28,985
I'm not your son, so I'll hold back.

434
00:30:32,489 --> 00:30:33,532
Solaad...

435
00:30:33,990 --> 00:30:35,450
What happened to you?

436
00:30:40,163 --> 00:30:41,790
- What was that?
- Over there!

437
00:30:43,124 --> 00:30:46,086
If something happens to Egg Rock,
we're in trouble.

438
00:30:46,419 --> 00:30:47,629
- Let's go!
- Yes, sir!

439
00:30:48,338 --> 00:30:51,174
I want a detailed explanation
from you later.

440
00:30:56,179 --> 00:30:57,305
What's happening?

441
00:30:57,597 --> 00:30:59,390
Part of the rock broke apart.

442
00:30:59,391 --> 00:31:00,850
Check the area!

443
00:31:02,477 --> 00:31:04,604
Someone, help...

444
00:31:05,438 --> 00:31:06,856
I'm going to die...

445
00:31:07,232 --> 00:31:08,232
Hey!

446
00:31:08,567 --> 00:31:10,443
Are you all right? What happened?

447
00:31:11,152 --> 00:31:14,114
I'm so hungry... So hungry...

448
00:31:14,656 --> 00:31:15,907
I'm going to die!

449
00:31:16,199 --> 00:31:19,202
"Hungry"? Hey, do you have anything
we can feed him?

450
00:31:19,953 --> 00:31:21,121
What's wrong?

451
00:31:21,329 --> 00:31:22,497
Feed me.

452
00:31:23,540 --> 00:31:26,376
You're asking us to feed you
at a time like this?

453
00:31:32,674 --> 00:31:34,092
Th-The Demon Clan!

454
00:31:41,141 --> 00:31:42,183
What's happening?

455
00:31:42,809 --> 00:31:43,851
We're gonna die!

456
00:31:43,852 --> 00:31:47,147
Where do you think you're going.
You're my lunch!

457
00:31:50,358 --> 00:31:51,860
The Egg Rock seems safe.

458
00:31:52,027 --> 00:31:54,404
It must be a harbinger
of the Year of Doom.

459
00:31:59,451 --> 00:32:01,244
Voltaic Whip!

460
00:32:07,208 --> 00:32:09,127
I'm still hungry!

461
00:32:12,047 --> 00:32:13,173
Master Zoria!

462
00:32:13,548 --> 00:32:15,967
We are the guardians
of the Sky Temple!

463
00:32:16,343 --> 00:32:18,844
Now that I, the Head Warrior,
Zoria is here,

464
00:32:18,845 --> 00:32:20,680
I won't let you have your way!

465
00:32:22,349 --> 00:32:24,559
I'll go get the
Winged Sword at once!

466
00:32:25,352 --> 00:32:26,352
Let's go!

467
00:32:31,524 --> 00:32:35,278
I have defeated 65 Demons to date!

468
00:32:36,446 --> 00:32:38,615
Behold!
My Celestial Spear Technique!

469
00:32:41,159 --> 00:32:43,161
Celestial Spear Strike!

470
00:32:51,878 --> 00:32:52,878
How's that?

471
00:32:53,546 --> 00:32:56,549
Can't do... anything about it? Hm?

472
00:32:57,384 --> 00:32:59,886
I don't care how many you've killed.

473
00:33:00,220 --> 00:33:03,723
Don't think I'm like those
red or gray peons!

474
00:33:04,224 --> 00:33:05,266
This can't be...

475
00:33:09,813 --> 00:33:11,314
- Wait!
- Mistress Vaness!

476
00:33:11,564 --> 00:33:12,564
Ellatte?

477
00:33:12,691 --> 00:33:13,942
The Demon Clan is here!

478
00:33:14,067 --> 00:33:15,235
What did you say?

479
00:33:21,991 --> 00:33:22,991
I have to go!

480
00:33:23,535 --> 00:33:24,619
Hey!

481
00:33:26,204 --> 00:33:27,204
This can't be!

482
00:33:35,004 --> 00:33:37,048
Get off your high horse!

483
00:33:37,590 --> 00:33:41,260
Don't you know I am Neckless Dahaka
of the Six Knights of Black?

484
00:33:41,261 --> 00:33:42,846
Or maybe you have a death wish?

485
00:33:47,726 --> 00:33:48,727
Now, die.

486
00:33:53,106 --> 00:33:55,108
So... laad...

487
00:33:57,610 --> 00:34:01,030
That's about enough.
Unless you want to die.

488
00:34:03,992 --> 00:34:06,995
You can't be serious, brat!

489
00:34:08,621 --> 00:34:10,832
As a reward for making me laugh,

490
00:34:11,082 --> 00:34:14,377
I'll kill you right now!

491
00:34:28,433 --> 00:34:29,934
Solaad and Master Zoria!

492
00:34:30,727 --> 00:34:32,479
Thunder Carnival!

493
00:34:33,980 --> 00:34:35,857
I'm gonna borrow this for a sec.

494
00:34:37,400 --> 00:34:38,400
Full Counter!

495
00:34:50,121 --> 00:34:51,121
Master Zoria!

496
00:34:54,292 --> 00:34:55,543
Looks like he's fine.

497
00:34:56,085 --> 00:34:58,505
- Um...
- Hey, Meliodas!

498
00:34:59,088 --> 00:35:01,049
There you are!

499
00:35:01,382 --> 00:35:02,675
Hey, Hawk!

500
00:35:03,134 --> 00:35:05,136
What happened to the Demon Clan?

501
00:35:08,431 --> 00:35:10,683
What the heck is this?

502
00:35:10,809 --> 00:35:11,809
Over there!

503
00:35:18,399 --> 00:35:20,193
The fallen men...

504
00:35:20,819 --> 00:35:22,403
I knew it!

505
00:35:24,155 --> 00:35:25,155
Granny.

506
00:35:26,282 --> 00:35:27,867
The Great Oshiro!

507
00:35:28,243 --> 00:35:29,243
Hm?

508
00:35:29,369 --> 00:35:32,997
The Great Oshiro has defeated
the Demon!

509
00:35:33,122 --> 00:35:35,124
What?

510
00:35:36,543 --> 00:35:38,920
So this is salt-roasted sky fish?

511
00:35:41,256 --> 00:35:46,386
I feel blessed to be able
to share a drink with my son.

512
00:35:48,304 --> 00:35:49,806
Oh, this is pretty good.

513
00:35:50,390 --> 00:35:51,933
It's your favorite.

514
00:35:52,475 --> 00:35:54,811
Here, have mine as well.

515
00:35:55,186 --> 00:35:57,564
Oh, well if you insist.

516
00:36:00,191 --> 00:36:04,028
I didn't realize you've even
surpassed me as a warrior.

517
00:36:04,153 --> 00:36:08,032
Let me guess,
you've been secretly training!

518
00:36:12,078 --> 00:36:13,788
Listen up, everyone!

519
00:36:14,914 --> 00:36:17,208
Now we can follow the Celestial Law,

520
00:36:17,333 --> 00:36:21,754
and my son can continue
with the Succession Ceremony.

521
00:36:24,549 --> 00:36:26,133
Succession Ceremony?

522
00:36:26,134 --> 00:36:29,554
Go ahead, Ellatte,
go to your fiancé!

523
00:36:42,609 --> 00:36:46,487
The Great Oshiro!

524
00:36:48,156 --> 00:36:52,243
The Great Oshiro!

525
00:36:52,744 --> 00:36:53,744
Oh, how today...

526
00:36:53,828 --> 00:36:55,121
What are you doing, Hawk?

527
00:36:57,957 --> 00:37:00,960
I am the Great Oshiro, you rud...
Ow!

528
00:37:01,419 --> 00:37:03,713
- Ow!
- Say that again, pig.

529
00:37:03,838 --> 00:37:05,923
Sorry...

530
00:37:05,924 --> 00:37:08,551
That was outstanding work, Solaad!

531
00:37:09,052 --> 00:37:13,347
This esteemed creature you've brought
back with you turned out to be

532
00:37:13,348 --> 00:37:17,143
the legendary Great Oshiro
that saved us 3,000 years ago.

533
00:37:18,561 --> 00:37:21,439
Behold this lovable form.

534
00:37:21,731 --> 00:37:25,944
It's exactly as
depicted on our walls.

535
00:37:26,069 --> 00:37:28,488
So smooth and round!

536
00:37:28,738 --> 00:37:30,198
He's not white.

537
00:37:32,492 --> 00:37:35,078
It's true, he is not white.

538
00:37:35,870 --> 00:37:37,372
Is he an imposter?

539
00:37:40,249 --> 00:37:44,252
Lo and behold! I am the blood
descendant of the Great Oshiro.

540
00:37:44,253 --> 00:37:45,463
I am the Great Opink!

541
00:37:45,838 --> 00:37:47,340
That's kind of a stretch.

542
00:37:47,590 --> 00:37:49,592
Oh, the Great Opink!

543
00:37:50,009 --> 00:37:52,679
All of you, this is the Great Opink!

544
00:37:53,137 --> 00:37:54,222
Yeah, no...

545
00:38:02,730 --> 00:38:06,651
Yahoo! This feels so good!

546
00:38:06,901 --> 00:38:09,362
The land looks so small from here!

547
00:38:09,654 --> 00:38:11,948
I love giant Diane...

548
00:38:12,699 --> 00:38:15,159
but little Diane is cute too.

549
00:38:15,952 --> 00:38:20,039
Who would've thought this would
happen? If I return empty-handed...

550
00:38:20,748 --> 00:38:23,084
But I'm worried about everyone too.

551
00:38:24,293 --> 00:38:25,878
What should I do?

552
00:38:33,511 --> 00:38:35,263
The Great Opink?

553
00:38:35,680 --> 00:38:37,890
Your mouth just runs, doesn't it?

554
00:38:38,016 --> 00:38:40,977
I couldn't help it! This is so good!

555
00:38:45,398 --> 00:38:47,525
This is the battledress
for Celestial warriors.

556
00:38:55,324 --> 00:38:57,952
Thanks, I was feeling a bit chilly.

557
00:38:58,536 --> 00:39:00,872
You're not Solaad, are you?

558
00:39:01,497 --> 00:39:03,582
I told you that in the beginning.

559
00:39:03,583 --> 00:39:05,459
A troublesome case
of mistaken identity.

560
00:39:05,460 --> 00:39:06,586
Then who are you?

561
00:39:07,587 --> 00:39:09,088
I'm just a pub owner.

562
00:39:09,672 --> 00:39:12,091
And I'm Captain Leftovers!

563
00:39:12,383 --> 00:39:14,969
What's that?
What did you come here for?

564
00:39:15,094 --> 00:39:19,015
We didn't come because we wanted to.
We don't know how to get back.

565
00:39:21,809 --> 00:39:22,810
Um...

566
00:39:24,520 --> 00:39:29,192
I want you to keep pretending to be Solaad
until the noon Succession Ceremony!

567
00:39:29,859 --> 00:39:33,571
The ceremony is sacred to us,
the Celestials.

568
00:39:34,197 --> 00:39:36,240
In order to stand
against the Demon Clan,

569
00:39:36,365 --> 00:39:39,202
for generations, the son of the
Head Warrior has inherited

570
00:39:39,327 --> 00:39:41,329
the Winged Sword at
the Succession Ceremony.

571
00:39:41,537 --> 00:39:45,625
This law has been followed by the
Celestials for thousands of years.

572
00:39:47,835 --> 00:39:53,716
I understand it's law,
but that old man was really angry.

573
00:39:54,467 --> 00:39:57,845
There's a reason why Master Zoria
despises the Demon Clan.

574
00:39:59,013 --> 00:40:01,682
A hundred years ago,
during the last Year of Doom,

575
00:40:01,808 --> 00:40:05,394
Master Zoria's wife,
Solaad's mother, passed away.

576
00:40:06,020 --> 00:40:08,439
She got caught in the battle
against the Demon Clan.

577
00:40:09,774 --> 00:40:13,610
I see. That's why he got angry
when his son ran.

578
00:40:13,611 --> 00:40:16,989
He didn't run!
He left because he had a plan.

579
00:40:17,448 --> 00:40:19,117
Solaad is kind.

580
00:40:19,700 --> 00:40:20,868
Solaad is...

581
00:40:22,495 --> 00:40:24,038
I know he'll come back.

582
00:40:24,330 --> 00:40:27,333
Can't someone else do the ceremony?

583
00:40:27,542 --> 00:40:30,378
It has to be Solaad! He promised me!

584
00:40:30,795 --> 00:40:32,755
Promise? I thought it was law.

585
00:40:35,716 --> 00:40:37,510
Wh-What's so funny?

586
00:40:38,427 --> 00:40:41,722
If he's not back by noon tomorrow,
then you're on your own.

587
00:40:43,141 --> 00:40:44,142
Then...

588
00:40:45,768 --> 00:40:46,602
Right?

589
00:40:46,727 --> 00:40:48,187
Leave it to us!

590
00:40:59,866 --> 00:41:01,575
The Winged Sword...

591
00:41:01,576 --> 00:41:04,787
You and I are inheriting
this together. Right, Solaad?

592
00:41:12,295 --> 00:41:14,297
For generations,

593
00:41:14,463 --> 00:41:17,758
our ancestors have passed down
the Winged Sword...

594
00:41:18,551 --> 00:41:20,887
Including Mother and Father...

595
00:41:22,138 --> 00:41:23,138
That's right.

596
00:41:25,433 --> 00:41:27,852
This is a special Year of Doom.

597
00:41:28,227 --> 00:41:32,648
No one believes it, but this is the year
the Great Oshiro's seal will break.

598
00:41:33,191 --> 00:41:34,525
That again?

599
00:41:35,568 --> 00:41:37,737
I've been studying it for years now.

600
00:41:38,362 --> 00:41:39,739
This mural...

601
00:41:40,489 --> 00:41:44,118
- But there are things I still don't...
- Solaad.

602
00:41:45,703 --> 00:41:47,246
What are you doing there?

603
00:41:49,165 --> 00:41:50,458
Listen, Father!

604
00:41:50,666 --> 00:41:54,503
At this rate, we will all be
destroyed by the Demon Clan!

605
00:41:54,879 --> 00:41:57,255
That is why you must train.

606
00:41:57,256 --> 00:41:59,300
It's different this time!

607
00:42:01,469 --> 00:42:04,931
I will not call a
law-breaking coward my son!

608
00:42:05,640 --> 00:42:09,936
He abandoned the village. How can
he be the son of the Head Warrior?

609
00:42:10,394 --> 00:42:12,063
What did he go to Earth for?

610
00:42:12,188 --> 00:42:14,481
There was no Great
Oshiro, was there?

611
00:42:14,482 --> 00:42:15,900
He abandoned us.

612
00:42:16,359 --> 00:42:18,402
No! Everyone, it's not true!

613
00:42:19,153 --> 00:42:21,781
I never thought this would happen!

614
00:42:32,583 --> 00:42:33,583
Elle?

615
00:42:36,045 --> 00:42:38,047
Elizabeth...

616
00:42:38,589 --> 00:42:40,049
How are you feeling?

617
00:42:40,925 --> 00:42:43,010
You sounded like
you were having a bad dream.

618
00:42:44,136 --> 00:42:45,136
I'm sorry.

619
00:42:47,765 --> 00:42:52,311
I just wanted to know
what was in a Celestial's heart.

620
00:42:56,148 --> 00:42:59,944
So, your Ellatte and
I look that alike?

621
00:43:00,069 --> 00:43:01,069
Yeah.

622
00:43:01,862 --> 00:43:04,156
You're much more gentle, though.

623
00:43:06,534 --> 00:43:07,618
Solaad...

624
00:43:08,077 --> 00:43:11,455
you came here to find a way
to save your land, right?

625
00:43:12,206 --> 00:43:16,419
But I'm heading back
without having done anything.

626
00:43:17,545 --> 00:43:20,673
What you've started
is not meaningless.

627
00:43:21,132 --> 00:43:24,343
If Meliodas were here,
I'm sure that's what he'd say.

628
00:43:27,430 --> 00:43:29,932
I wanted to save
the Kingdom of Liones too.

629
00:43:30,308 --> 00:43:33,811
I journeyed on my own in search
of the Seven Deadly Sins.

630
00:43:34,520 --> 00:43:35,520
You, too?

631
00:43:36,814 --> 00:43:38,816
The journey was a reckless one.

632
00:43:39,525 --> 00:43:44,447
But the one who saved
powerless old me was Meliodas.

633
00:43:46,532 --> 00:43:47,908
Meliodas told me,

634
00:43:48,159 --> 00:43:51,620
it's because I went on the journey
to try to save everyone

635
00:43:52,163 --> 00:43:54,832
that I was able to find
the Seven Deadly Sins.

636
00:43:55,374 --> 00:43:58,294
Nothing would have started,
if I had done nothing.

637
00:44:00,129 --> 00:44:01,672
That's what he told me.

638
00:44:03,049 --> 00:44:07,094
- Meliodas sounds like an amazing person.
- He is!

639
00:44:08,346 --> 00:44:09,513
But I...

640
00:44:10,222 --> 00:44:12,224
I can't be like Meliodas.

641
00:44:12,808 --> 00:44:16,062
Ha! Of course not, coward.

642
00:44:16,854 --> 00:44:17,854
Ban!

643
00:44:18,272 --> 00:44:21,400
You ran just because you thought
no one understands.

644
00:44:22,026 --> 00:44:24,028
N-No! It wasn't like that!

645
00:44:24,362 --> 00:44:27,948
You abandoned those
tied down to rules.

646
00:44:28,282 --> 00:44:31,410
I came because I want to
protect Elle and everyone!

647
00:44:32,870 --> 00:44:35,581
Do you really think
you have the resolve?

648
00:44:36,457 --> 00:44:37,958
If it's to protect everyone...

649
00:44:39,085 --> 00:44:41,837
I'll do anything!

650
00:44:45,341 --> 00:44:47,676
It's easy to talk.

651
00:44:53,557 --> 00:44:54,557
Hm?

652
00:44:54,642 --> 00:44:56,602
I thought you were...

653
00:44:57,228 --> 00:44:58,562
fighting?

654
00:45:00,147 --> 00:45:02,900
The human heart is
a mysterious thing.

655
00:45:14,328 --> 00:45:18,040
Miss Ellatte, you look beautiful.

656
00:45:18,374 --> 00:45:21,419
Master Solaad has grown impressive
as well.

657
00:45:22,336 --> 00:45:23,587
It is time.

658
00:45:24,213 --> 00:45:25,714
Ready? Let's go.

659
00:45:25,923 --> 00:45:26,923
Sure!

660
00:45:45,276 --> 00:45:48,154
The apple pie is ready everyone!

661
00:45:48,863 --> 00:45:50,865
It looks delicious!

662
00:45:51,115 --> 00:45:53,242
Let's eat while we can.

663
00:45:56,370 --> 00:45:58,414
It looks perfect...

664
00:46:07,131 --> 00:46:08,174
Not bad.

665
00:46:11,719 --> 00:46:13,762
This is really tasty!

666
00:46:13,971 --> 00:46:16,932
Why don't you take this place over
since the captain's gone?

667
00:46:17,057 --> 00:46:20,686
In which case, profits will increase
by 300 percent.

668
00:46:22,938 --> 00:46:23,938
What happened?

669
00:46:24,190 --> 00:46:25,608
- Merlin...
- I know.

670
00:46:26,192 --> 00:46:29,487
I sense abnormal magic ahead.
It's coming from our right.

671
00:46:30,696 --> 00:46:34,241
We will continue to charge ahead.
We're close to our destination.

672
00:46:34,575 --> 00:46:36,368
Everyone, prepare to land.

673
00:47:12,571 --> 00:47:13,696
Here and now,

674
00:47:13,697 --> 00:47:17,826
our greatest treasure, which has long
continued to suppress the Demon Clan,

675
00:47:18,160 --> 00:47:20,246
will now be handed down to my son!

676
00:47:28,629 --> 00:47:29,755
This is...

677
00:47:31,882 --> 00:47:33,592
Geez, what are you doing?

678
00:47:40,516 --> 00:47:42,059
What is the meaning of this?

679
00:47:48,148 --> 00:47:51,693
What's going on?
That huge egg just broke!

680
00:47:51,694 --> 00:47:52,987
Was that supposed to happen?

681
00:47:56,323 --> 00:47:57,323
That's...

682
00:47:57,408 --> 00:47:58,408
The Demon Clan!

683
00:47:58,409 --> 00:47:59,951
The seal has been broken!

684
00:47:59,952 --> 00:48:01,370
There's so many of them!

685
00:48:02,871 --> 00:48:03,955
But why?

686
00:48:03,956 --> 00:48:06,584
The Resurrection Day was supposed
to be much later!

687
00:48:07,710 --> 00:48:09,920
All of you, have no fear!

688
00:48:10,045 --> 00:48:12,673
We have the Great Opink with us!

689
00:48:12,881 --> 00:48:15,593
Are you serious?
This wasn't part of the deal!

690
00:48:16,051 --> 00:48:17,927
The ceremony will have to wait.

691
00:48:17,928 --> 00:48:20,556
This is the day we have trained for.

692
00:48:20,931 --> 00:48:27,271
Now, we will follow the Ancient Law
and rid our land of the Demon Clan!

693
00:48:33,068 --> 00:48:36,196
Celestial Sword Style,
Celestial Beast Slice!

694
00:48:44,997 --> 00:48:45,997
Miss Ellatte!

695
00:48:46,290 --> 00:48:47,625
Evacuate everyone!

696
00:48:47,750 --> 00:48:48,959
You need to as well.

697
00:48:49,084 --> 00:48:50,919
I am a Celestial warrior too.

698
00:48:51,128 --> 00:48:52,880
They're too much for you.

699
00:48:53,505 --> 00:48:55,466
It doesn't matter.

700
00:48:55,716 --> 00:48:58,969
This is my home,
and I will protect it!

701
00:49:00,554 --> 00:49:03,140
Good grief. What a spitfire!

702
00:49:21,367 --> 00:49:22,868
What a fine resurrection.

703
00:49:22,993 --> 00:49:26,664
Oh, who's the nitwit who
got the head start?

704
00:49:28,248 --> 00:49:32,710
I don't sense Dahaka anymore.
He must have been eliminated.

705
00:49:32,711 --> 00:49:36,590
The power is weak, but this island
is full of it.

706
00:49:36,924 --> 00:49:39,093
And that's not all.

707
00:49:39,385 --> 00:49:43,597
I sense one huge power.
I'll take that one.

708
00:49:43,806 --> 00:49:46,350
Tsk, that's not fair. Tsk!

709
00:49:47,851 --> 00:49:51,188
You're telling us to be satisfied
with the souls of peons?

710
00:49:51,772 --> 00:49:56,275
If we collect all of the souls,
we will be resurrected.

711
00:49:56,276 --> 00:49:59,530
I will begin preparations for the
resurrection ceremony.

712
00:50:00,114 --> 00:50:02,574
For our most precious wish!

713
00:50:02,908 --> 00:50:05,744
Time for the festivities to begin!

714
00:50:07,204 --> 00:50:08,330
What is that?

715
00:50:11,750 --> 00:50:15,128
Oh, how lovely!
There's one with some potential.

716
00:50:15,129 --> 00:50:16,129
Name yourself!

717
00:50:16,505 --> 00:50:18,882
I am Gara of the Six
Knights of Black.

718
00:50:19,049 --> 00:50:21,342
Don't get ahead of yourself,
my sacrificial lamb.

719
00:50:21,343 --> 00:50:23,095
Do you need someone to play with?

720
00:50:23,429 --> 00:50:27,141
You can come in hordes,
but we will get rid of you all!

721
00:50:28,892 --> 00:50:31,895
I'm sorry, but I don't like
hotheaded guys.

722
00:50:32,020 --> 00:50:33,814
Why don't you play with them?

723
00:50:44,616 --> 00:50:47,369
Descendants of the Goddess Clan!

724
00:50:49,037 --> 00:50:51,540
You're just an appetizer
before the feast!

725
00:50:54,585 --> 00:50:58,172
Your dirty little souls
will all be devoured by me,

726
00:50:58,505 --> 00:51:00,507
Mr. Derocchio himself!

727
00:51:12,436 --> 00:51:16,356
O great beast who has
been sealed alongside us,

728
00:51:17,149 --> 00:51:22,196
I now offer you the souls of the
descendants of the Goddess Clan.

729
00:51:22,780 --> 00:51:26,408
Awaken, O great beast!

730
00:51:35,751 --> 00:51:37,169
Evacuate to the plaza!

731
00:51:37,294 --> 00:51:38,378
O-Okay.

732
00:51:48,305 --> 00:51:50,390
Tsk! See, they're all peons.

733
00:51:50,849 --> 00:51:53,936
And... there's another peon.

734
00:51:56,980 --> 00:51:58,524
Should I kill her at once?

735
00:51:58,649 --> 00:52:01,360
Or should I make her suffer first?

736
00:52:11,578 --> 00:52:13,664
Hmm, how about this?

737
00:52:21,088 --> 00:52:24,132
I know, you're the one
Bellion wants to play with.

738
00:52:24,633 --> 00:52:25,633
Bellion?

739
00:52:27,302 --> 00:52:28,387
You have to run!

740
00:52:36,854 --> 00:52:38,729
Enjoying yourself, Pump?

741
00:52:38,730 --> 00:52:43,193
If you let me fight him,
then I'd enjoy myself.

742
00:52:47,447 --> 00:52:48,448
He's strong.

743
00:52:49,825 --> 00:52:50,826
That bastard!

744
00:52:51,910 --> 00:52:54,913
Most guys would die from that hit.

745
00:52:55,205 --> 00:52:57,374
I'm impressed... human.

746
00:52:58,000 --> 00:53:01,628
That's right, Bellion,
Six Knights of Black.

747
00:53:02,754 --> 00:53:05,841
So you know my name!

748
00:53:10,053 --> 00:53:11,846
Let me go!

749
00:53:11,847 --> 00:53:14,849
Now, it's time to do your job,
Great Opink!

750
00:53:14,850 --> 00:53:17,435
No way! I seriously don't wanna!

751
00:53:17,436 --> 00:53:21,106
And you call yourself
the Great Oshiro's descendant?

752
00:53:24,776 --> 00:53:26,111
What's this?

753
00:53:27,529 --> 00:53:29,323
Hmph! How annoying.

754
00:53:30,282 --> 00:53:32,701
A statue of that monster?

755
00:53:32,993 --> 00:53:36,997
The fools who worship that thing
need to be obliterated.

756
00:53:37,539 --> 00:53:39,832
He's huge! Let's run, Granny!

757
00:53:39,833 --> 00:53:41,084
You!

758
00:53:41,335 --> 00:53:45,756
How dare you do that to the Great
Oshiro, you shameless heathen!

759
00:53:46,173 --> 00:53:50,218
Come forth light,
and destroy the darkness!

760
00:53:50,427 --> 00:53:51,470
Ark!

761
00:53:51,970 --> 00:53:53,138
Crap!

762
00:53:54,139 --> 00:53:55,599
What was that?

763
00:53:55,891 --> 00:53:58,310
That crappy move is called Ark?

764
00:53:58,435 --> 00:54:00,562
My Ark didn't work?

765
00:54:00,729 --> 00:54:01,729
Buzz off!

766
00:54:02,189 --> 00:54:03,774
Freeze Storm!

767
00:54:04,650 --> 00:54:05,650
Granny!

768
00:54:07,277 --> 00:54:11,031
The Goddess Clan has fallen low
after 3,000 years.

769
00:54:11,490 --> 00:54:13,116
Now, the finishing move!

770
00:54:13,325 --> 00:54:15,911
Hey, hold on there,
lion-faced old man!

771
00:54:16,954 --> 00:54:20,707
You've angered the one guy
you shouldn't have.

772
00:54:22,417 --> 00:54:24,419
I've seen this form somewhere...

773
00:54:24,711 --> 00:54:26,253
No, it can't be.

774
00:54:26,254 --> 00:54:31,426
Thought I might need this someday.
Merlin's special Monster Block!

775
00:54:32,803 --> 00:54:34,346
Transpork!

776
00:54:35,097 --> 00:54:36,640
Tyrant Dragon!

777
00:54:40,352 --> 00:54:42,145
- Dragon?
<i>- </i>Dragon.

778
00:54:42,729 --> 00:54:46,566
- Dragon?
- Yes, dragon! I keep telling you!

779
00:54:47,025 --> 00:54:48,986
I'll roast you alive!

780
00:54:49,194 --> 00:54:50,570
Dragon Breath!

781
00:54:53,031 --> 00:54:55,033
Hot!

782
00:54:56,660 --> 00:54:59,246
How dare you make a
mockery of Derocchio!

783
00:55:00,205 --> 00:55:01,790
Transpork!

784
00:55:03,750 --> 00:55:05,502
Sand Crawler!

785
00:55:07,045 --> 00:55:11,133
Hey, Lion Man! You can't catch me!

786
00:55:17,180 --> 00:55:19,725
Hey, that's cheating!

787
00:55:21,810 --> 00:55:23,270
Transpork!

788
00:55:23,770 --> 00:55:25,105
Devil Manta!

789
00:55:25,355 --> 00:55:26,355
I'm gonna...

790
00:55:26,606 --> 00:55:27,606
Granny!

791
00:55:28,066 --> 00:55:29,067
Hold on!

792
00:55:29,901 --> 00:55:31,737
Playtime is over!

793
00:55:32,112 --> 00:55:33,613
Ice Meteor!

794
00:55:36,033 --> 00:55:38,326
Stop that!

795
00:55:40,412 --> 00:55:41,412
Interesting.

796
00:55:41,913 --> 00:55:46,334
Looks like I won't get bored
while the peon souls get cooked.

797
00:55:46,835 --> 00:55:49,378
Until we've prepared
for the resurrection ritual,

798
00:55:49,379 --> 00:55:51,757
you can keep me entertained!

799
00:55:54,342 --> 00:55:55,677
Sorry, but...

800
00:55:56,219 --> 00:55:59,181
it looks like we're
one step ahead of you.

801
00:55:59,514 --> 00:56:00,640
What?

802
00:56:10,692 --> 00:56:11,693
I'm back...

803
00:56:12,277 --> 00:56:13,361
to the Sky Temple!

804
00:56:14,613 --> 00:56:15,781
The Demon Clan!

805
00:56:16,156 --> 00:56:17,157
Ellatte...

806
00:56:17,282 --> 00:56:18,617
Get the lead out!

807
00:56:19,951 --> 00:56:23,705
You'll do anything to save
them, right? Then let's go!

808
00:56:24,164 --> 00:56:25,164
Okay!

809
00:56:27,959 --> 00:56:30,837
We're coming too! Merlin!

810
00:56:31,129 --> 00:56:32,172
Magic Cancel.

811
00:56:35,509 --> 00:56:36,509
Apport.

812
00:56:36,843 --> 00:56:39,596
We won't let Solaad's
friends get hurt!

813
00:56:39,763 --> 00:56:41,932
I'll head to the top of Craggy Peak.

814
00:56:42,349 --> 00:56:45,936
Let's see... Which one will make
an interesting opponent?

815
00:56:46,770 --> 00:56:49,523
Oh, a flying Captain Leftovers.

816
00:56:50,607 --> 00:56:52,526
Hawk! You're okay!

817
00:56:54,694 --> 00:56:56,113
Hot, hot!

818
00:56:56,279 --> 00:56:58,239
Glad you made it back.

819
00:56:58,240 --> 00:56:59,907
We're saved!

820
00:56:59,908 --> 00:57:01,243
What is that?

821
00:57:03,328 --> 00:57:06,164
I will be your opponent now.

822
00:57:08,041 --> 00:57:09,041
Crap!

823
00:57:10,836 --> 00:57:12,087
Fox Hunt!

824
00:57:14,214 --> 00:57:15,214
Ban!

825
00:57:22,556 --> 00:57:23,431
Who are you?

826
00:57:23,557 --> 00:57:25,016
The Seven Deadly Sins.

827
00:57:25,183 --> 00:57:26,643
We're friends of Solaad.

828
00:57:26,810 --> 00:57:28,979
- From Earth?
- We can talk later!

829
00:57:29,354 --> 00:57:31,565
First,
let's take care of these guys!

830
00:57:34,609 --> 00:57:36,820
Let me play some more.

831
00:57:38,363 --> 00:57:41,658
If I could just find an opening,
and get a hit in...

832
00:57:41,783 --> 00:57:43,702
I know what I'll do.

833
00:57:48,915 --> 00:57:49,915
That was nothing!

834
00:57:54,671 --> 00:57:57,632
<i>Huh, what am I doing?</i>

835
00:57:58,633 --> 00:58:00,552
<i>If I land at a time like this...</i>

836
00:58:02,554 --> 00:58:06,725
<i>I can't move.
My body... won't respond.</i>

837
00:58:07,142 --> 00:58:08,768
Hypno-Stinger.

838
00:58:08,977 --> 00:58:13,064
My needles will paralyze the spirit
of a living organism.

839
00:58:13,607 --> 00:58:17,277
Now, come and give me a hug!

840
00:58:17,903 --> 00:58:21,448
<i>No! I can't die like this!</i>

841
00:58:22,240 --> 00:58:23,450
<i>I don't want to die!</i>

842
00:58:25,035 --> 00:58:27,412
Solaad, help!

843
00:58:27,787 --> 00:58:29,206
Sorry I'm late, Elle.

844
00:58:32,918 --> 00:58:35,170
Solaad! Is it really you?

845
00:58:35,629 --> 00:58:37,797
I'm sorry I'm late, Elle.

846
00:58:38,798 --> 00:58:40,300
You idiot!

847
00:58:40,717 --> 00:58:44,054
I was... I was so worried about you!

848
00:58:44,888 --> 00:58:46,723
I'm not going anywhere.

849
00:58:47,557 --> 00:58:50,143
Idiot. Of course you're not.

850
00:58:52,020 --> 00:58:55,065
Tsk! Enough of that already!

851
00:58:55,857 --> 00:59:00,195
Tsk! She was about to give me a hug!

852
00:59:02,656 --> 00:59:03,531
Huh?

853
00:59:03,657 --> 00:59:07,869
They're having a heartwarming
reunion. Don't ruin it!

854
00:59:30,100 --> 00:59:34,228
Is that all you got?
I thought you were strong.

855
00:59:34,229 --> 00:59:35,605
Don't let your guard down!

856
00:59:35,939 --> 00:59:36,939
Huh?

857
00:59:38,566 --> 00:59:39,566
Geez...

858
00:59:44,322 --> 00:59:47,659
See, aren't you
starting to feel good?

859
00:59:48,493 --> 00:59:50,912
You're going to play with me, right?

860
00:59:51,204 --> 00:59:55,417
Then you can give me
a hug in her stead!

861
00:59:59,546 --> 01:00:01,756
That's one down!

862
01:00:03,508 --> 01:00:05,134
H-How did you...

863
01:00:05,135 --> 01:00:08,596
How can you still be alive
with needles all though your body?

864
01:00:09,764 --> 01:00:12,934
Why don't you just shut up,
Sea Urchin Dude?

865
01:00:13,143 --> 01:00:15,145
You wanted a hug, right?

866
01:00:23,737 --> 01:00:26,656
For a brat like you to know my name,

867
01:00:26,906 --> 01:00:31,286
I must have become famous
during the last 3,000 years!

868
01:00:35,665 --> 01:00:37,167
The Six Knights of Black.

869
01:00:37,542 --> 01:00:40,461
It's said you're as strong
as the Ten Commandments.

870
01:00:40,462 --> 01:00:43,840
Yet, you're so lawless,
even the Demon Lord abandoned you.

871
01:00:44,549 --> 01:00:45,717
Am I right?

872
01:00:46,676 --> 01:00:48,053
You bastard!

873
01:00:52,057 --> 01:00:56,144
I don't know who you are,
but you must want to die badly.

874
01:01:08,990 --> 01:01:13,203
My skills have surpassed that
of the Ten Commandments!

875
01:01:23,588 --> 01:01:27,092
The one who didn't choose me
to be in the Ten Commandments...

876
01:01:27,801 --> 01:01:28,968
Meliodas.

877
01:01:29,636 --> 01:01:31,513
I will never forgive him!

878
01:01:33,056 --> 01:01:34,057
Are you finished?

879
01:01:39,062 --> 01:01:41,815
Is this the one
collecting our souls?

880
01:01:42,190 --> 01:01:44,025
How dare you hurt our friends!

881
01:01:45,443 --> 01:01:46,819
My body...

882
01:01:46,820 --> 01:01:47,820
Won't move...

883
01:01:49,114 --> 01:01:52,158
Any filth that
approaches the ceremony

884
01:01:52,659 --> 01:01:55,829
will have their nerves destroyed
by my power.

885
01:01:58,164 --> 01:02:00,500
You're up to no good, aren't you?

886
01:02:01,000 --> 01:02:03,962
Goat's Sin of Lust,
Gowther, has arrived!

887
01:02:04,462 --> 01:02:05,839
Gattling Jack!

888
01:02:06,548 --> 01:02:08,550
Fight Fire With Fire!

889
01:02:08,716 --> 01:02:10,260
You're wasting your time.

890
01:02:20,437 --> 01:02:21,437
Gowther!

891
01:02:25,150 --> 01:02:26,234
Crap...

892
01:02:27,777 --> 01:02:30,488
I can't... control my body.

893
01:02:30,989 --> 01:02:33,116
Truly like a puppet.

894
01:02:33,950 --> 01:02:37,912
I will use you as sacrifices
for the resurrection.

895
01:02:38,037 --> 01:02:40,039
Damn it! This wasn't supposed to...

896
01:02:40,331 --> 01:02:42,000
There's nothing to be done.

897
01:02:55,263 --> 01:02:56,389
Wh-What?

898
01:03:03,396 --> 01:03:07,317
I'm getting consumed! Stop!

899
01:03:09,611 --> 01:03:11,112
Nightmare Terror.

900
01:03:11,321 --> 01:03:15,492
So, it was an illusion.
Why weren't your nerves affected?

901
01:03:15,950 --> 01:03:20,246
Unfortunately for you, I am a doll.
An attack on my nerves won't work.

902
01:03:21,414 --> 01:03:24,000
Spirit Spear Chastiefol.
Third Form.

903
01:03:24,167 --> 01:03:25,460
Fossilization!

904
01:03:42,143 --> 01:03:44,729
Oh, you're the true body!

905
01:03:45,104 --> 01:03:48,816
Thank you for playing
with my puppets.

906
01:03:48,983 --> 01:03:51,194
I must give you a reward!

907
01:03:51,736 --> 01:03:55,531
My whip will hold you in agony,
and you can dance to your death!

908
01:03:55,532 --> 01:03:57,199
Fresh Crush!

909
01:03:57,200 --> 01:03:58,201
Heavy Metal!

910
01:03:59,994 --> 01:04:02,497
You little brat!
It's not working on you!

911
01:04:02,956 --> 01:04:06,458
Sorry about that.
I think I'm a bad match for you.

912
01:04:06,459 --> 01:04:08,503
Don't apologize!

913
01:04:13,466 --> 01:04:16,344
What a perfect look
for a giant dimwit like you!

914
01:04:16,886 --> 01:04:18,263
What did you just say?

915
01:04:19,305 --> 01:04:21,933
I won't let anyone badmouth Diane!

916
01:04:26,646 --> 01:04:28,815
No Fire!

917
01:04:29,857 --> 01:04:30,857
C-Cold!

918
01:04:31,067 --> 01:04:33,069
What's happening?

919
01:04:33,987 --> 01:04:35,572
No Freeze!

920
01:04:35,738 --> 01:04:37,907
H-Hot, hot, hot!

921
01:04:38,783 --> 01:04:40,118
Fake Ball.

922
01:04:40,493 --> 01:04:43,955
A combination of attack
and illusion magic.

923
01:04:44,455 --> 01:04:47,292
I'd been wanting to test it out.

924
01:04:47,750 --> 01:04:50,169
No Fire, No Freeze!

925
01:04:50,587 --> 01:04:52,213
How about now?

926
01:04:53,381 --> 01:04:55,466
It's not just fire and ice.

927
01:05:02,015 --> 01:05:04,517
Then I'll just deal with all of it!

928
01:05:04,684 --> 01:05:06,978
Four Element Zero Barrier!

929
01:05:07,312 --> 01:05:08,730
Absolute Cancel.

930
01:05:12,317 --> 01:05:15,111
Hey, that's not fair!

931
01:05:17,405 --> 01:05:19,616
I hate annoying fights!

932
01:05:20,283 --> 01:05:23,286
You guys can play with her...
What?

933
01:05:27,624 --> 01:05:32,587
Oh? You came to me to be defeated.
I applaud your attitude.

934
01:05:32,795 --> 01:05:34,088
That can't be...

935
01:05:34,797 --> 01:05:37,383
Hey! Gara!

936
01:05:38,426 --> 01:05:39,844
In that case...

937
01:05:46,934 --> 01:05:48,186
How about this?

938
01:05:51,773 --> 01:05:54,525
There is no need to bother Merlin.

939
01:05:55,151 --> 01:05:57,278
I will be enough.

940
01:05:57,820 --> 01:06:01,240
You talk big for just a human!

941
01:06:01,741 --> 01:06:08,164
You are no match for me, Derocchio, the
Lion King of the Six Knights of Black!

942
01:06:08,289 --> 01:06:11,751
That you should call yourself the
king of the jungle in front of me...

943
01:06:11,876 --> 01:06:13,670
is presumptuous!

944
01:06:22,637 --> 01:06:25,056
What the heck, he's a monster!

945
01:06:26,307 --> 01:06:27,224
Crap!

946
01:06:27,225 --> 01:06:30,144
Double Hammer!

947
01:06:32,605 --> 01:06:33,605
Bumble Bee!

948
01:06:38,444 --> 01:06:39,611
Ready, King?

949
01:06:39,612 --> 01:06:40,612
Okay, Diane!

950
01:06:41,114 --> 01:06:42,115
Combination!

951
01:06:42,699 --> 01:06:44,075
Cross Shooting!

952
01:06:49,831 --> 01:06:50,831
Yes!

953
01:06:52,417 --> 01:06:54,419
They are the Seven Deadly Sins?

954
01:06:54,836 --> 01:06:56,670
I'm glad they're on our side.

955
01:06:56,671 --> 01:06:59,257
I cannot believe such people
were on Earth.

956
01:06:59,841 --> 01:07:03,761
So, what Solaad said was true.

957
01:07:04,470 --> 01:07:05,470
Master Zoria!

958
01:07:06,222 --> 01:07:09,642
- Solaad is battling the enemy leader!
- What?

959
01:07:10,643 --> 01:07:12,186
- Solaad!
- Master Zoria!

960
01:07:15,148 --> 01:07:17,525
- Is everyone safe?
- Where did my father go?

961
01:07:17,775 --> 01:07:18,943
Master Solaad?

962
01:07:19,068 --> 01:07:21,529
We heard you were battling
the Demon Clan.

963
01:07:21,863 --> 01:07:22,863
Huh?

964
01:07:29,370 --> 01:07:32,790
You're that upset about not being
chosen to be a Ten Commandment?

965
01:07:33,750 --> 01:07:35,209
What would you know?

966
01:07:36,294 --> 01:07:41,090
Someone who's still hung up on that,
will probably never be chosen.

967
01:07:41,632 --> 01:07:42,633
What did you say?

968
01:07:47,722 --> 01:07:48,723
I'm finishing you!

969
01:07:52,894 --> 01:07:54,479
Guess you're not getting it.

970
01:07:55,229 --> 01:07:56,229
You're...

971
01:07:57,190 --> 01:07:59,192
a Demon?

972
01:08:01,110 --> 01:08:02,528
Solaad!

973
01:08:04,447 --> 01:08:05,447
Stop, old man!

974
01:08:05,782 --> 01:08:08,159
I cannot let Solaad die!

975
01:08:08,451 --> 01:08:09,535
Run!

976
01:08:29,639 --> 01:08:30,639
Old man!

977
01:08:30,848 --> 01:08:32,892
What is that sword?

978
01:08:33,601 --> 01:08:38,564
For 3,000 years, it has been passed
down by our clan, this Winged Sword.

979
01:08:38,773 --> 01:08:41,818
Against this sword,
even the Demon Clan...

980
01:08:44,111 --> 01:08:45,363
Don't push yourself.

981
01:08:46,113 --> 01:08:47,113
Solaad...

982
01:08:49,575 --> 01:08:51,577
You stand back...

983
01:09:03,130 --> 01:09:04,130
What have I done?

984
01:09:04,507 --> 01:09:07,051
I killed my son with my own hands.

985
01:09:26,362 --> 01:09:29,574
A sword meant to kill Demons.
I see.

986
01:09:29,699 --> 01:09:31,450
It works well on you.

987
01:09:34,078 --> 01:09:35,454
How ironic.

988
01:09:36,080 --> 01:09:40,001
You're going to die by the weapon
of those you wanted to protect!

989
01:09:41,878 --> 01:09:43,588
What are you doing?

990
01:09:44,630 --> 01:09:45,673
Captain!

991
01:09:46,007 --> 01:09:47,008
Captain!

992
01:09:51,929 --> 01:09:53,805
Damn it, he disappeared!

993
01:09:53,806 --> 01:09:54,806
Over here!

994
01:09:55,516 --> 01:09:57,184
Father! Father!

995
01:09:57,435 --> 01:09:58,435
Master Zoria!

996
01:10:01,689 --> 01:10:03,232
The captain can't be...

997
01:10:03,774 --> 01:10:07,069
Captain! Captain...!

998
01:10:11,198 --> 01:10:12,366
Hey!

999
01:10:13,034 --> 01:10:15,119
Is everyone okay?

1000
01:10:16,120 --> 01:10:17,120
Hawk, over there!

1001
01:10:17,955 --> 01:10:18,955
Meliodas!

1002
01:10:25,046 --> 01:10:28,674
Meliodas! How can this have happened,
when I've finally found you?

1003
01:10:29,550 --> 01:10:31,552
I won't forgive you if you die.

1004
01:10:32,678 --> 01:10:34,346
Meliodas!

1005
01:10:34,347 --> 01:10:37,141
Who'll give me leftovers if you die!

1006
01:10:37,725 --> 01:10:39,644
How could the captain lose?

1007
01:10:39,769 --> 01:10:42,521
Crap! Don't let a guy
like that beat you.

1008
01:10:43,356 --> 01:10:45,775
He'll be okay, right, Merlin?

1009
01:10:46,025 --> 01:10:48,694
The captain won't die so easy.

1010
01:10:49,070 --> 01:10:52,865
But this sword appears
to be quite dangerous.

1011
01:10:53,658 --> 01:10:55,076
Do not fret.

1012
01:10:55,201 --> 01:10:58,746
This is due to the hidden power
of the Winged Sword.

1013
01:10:59,038 --> 01:11:01,374
Do something, Granny!

1014
01:11:01,999 --> 01:11:06,921
This sword can only be handled
by the Head Warrior.

1015
01:11:07,630 --> 01:11:11,217
As soon as Zoria's wounds are
healed, we'll bring him here.

1016
01:11:11,676 --> 01:11:14,053
Solaad...

1017
01:11:14,345 --> 01:11:16,055
- Master Zoria!
- Father!

1018
01:11:19,725 --> 01:11:20,725
Solaad!

1019
01:11:21,560 --> 01:11:22,561
You are all right?

1020
01:11:23,145 --> 01:11:25,898
I'm sorry I returned late.

1021
01:11:26,107 --> 01:11:28,317
What about your injury?

1022
01:11:30,987 --> 01:11:33,781
Huh, Solaad? And Ellatte too?

1023
01:11:35,408 --> 01:11:36,528
What is the meaning of this?

1024
01:11:37,034 --> 01:11:39,828
The one who looks like looks
like Ellatte is Elizabeth.

1025
01:11:39,829 --> 01:11:42,456
And the one who looks like Solaad
is Meliodas.

1026
01:11:43,165 --> 01:11:46,794
Around them are Meliodas's friends,
whom I met on Earth.

1027
01:11:47,211 --> 01:11:48,671
The Seven Deadly Sins.

1028
01:11:50,965 --> 01:11:54,218
It is hard to believe,
but it seems I must accept it.

1029
01:11:54,427 --> 01:11:56,886
During the fight
against the Demon Clan,

1030
01:11:56,887 --> 01:12:01,183
I am embarrassed to admit as Head
Warrior that they were of great help.

1031
01:12:03,394 --> 01:12:06,355
Ellatte, my wounds are fine now.

1032
01:12:06,939 --> 01:12:08,983
Please save Meliodas.

1033
01:12:09,150 --> 01:12:10,066
Okay!

1034
01:12:10,067 --> 01:12:12,737
Solaad, pull the sword from him.

1035
01:12:13,279 --> 01:12:15,948
Starting today,
you are the successor.

1036
01:12:16,866 --> 01:12:17,866
I understand.

1037
01:12:20,286 --> 01:12:21,537
I'll help you!

1038
01:12:21,704 --> 01:12:23,539
- You're...
- I'm Ellatte!

1039
01:12:24,123 --> 01:12:25,833
I will pull out the sword.

1040
01:12:26,125 --> 01:12:28,252
- Focus your healing power on the wound.
- Okay!

1041
01:12:31,547 --> 01:12:35,342
In our time of need, there are
two Solaads and two Ellattes.

1042
01:12:35,468 --> 01:12:38,596
And the Great Oshiro's reincarnation
as well.

1043
01:12:39,138 --> 01:12:42,600
This must be by the hands
of the Great Oshiro!

1044
01:12:48,397 --> 01:12:49,397
This is...

1045
01:12:49,690 --> 01:12:52,401
The sword is shining white.

1046
01:12:53,611 --> 01:12:54,779
Can it be?

1047
01:13:07,083 --> 01:13:11,670
All of the Six Knights of Black
have been destroyed except for me.

1048
01:13:12,254 --> 01:13:14,548
Those damn Seven Deadly Sins!

1049
01:13:15,216 --> 01:13:19,719
I had planned to sacrifice all
of the Celestial souls,

1050
01:13:19,720 --> 01:13:21,138
but I have no other choice now.

1051
01:13:22,389 --> 01:13:26,644
Dahaka, Gara, Derocchio, Pump, Atra.

1052
01:13:27,228 --> 01:13:29,563
In order to fulfill our wish,

1053
01:13:30,022 --> 01:13:32,441
I will borrow your souls.

1054
01:13:34,568 --> 01:13:37,113
Break the seal on the Great Beast!

1055
01:13:37,571 --> 01:13:40,282
O maleficient star sealed by
Mother Chaos,

1056
01:13:40,991 --> 01:13:44,078
I offer you the souls
of the Six Knights of Black!

1057
01:13:44,537 --> 01:13:48,833
Indura! Your heavy chains shall be
completely unbound!

1058
01:13:58,717 --> 01:14:01,554
What sinister magic!

1059
01:14:03,430 --> 01:14:06,100
It's even affecting me!

1060
01:14:09,937 --> 01:14:14,275
Now, Indura, we shall ahhihilate
those odious Celestials

1061
01:14:14,650 --> 01:14:18,070
who have kept us sealed
away for so long!

1062
01:14:29,456 --> 01:14:32,126
- What's that?
- The magical power is immense!

1063
01:14:36,088 --> 01:14:37,882
Merlin, what is that?

1064
01:14:38,132 --> 01:14:39,842
An Indura of Retribution.

1065
01:14:40,676 --> 01:14:42,469
They live in the Demon Realm,

1066
01:14:42,636 --> 01:14:46,182
where they roam wild,
controlled only by instinct.

1067
01:14:46,640 --> 01:14:49,018
It's said they even prey
on the Demon Clan.

1068
01:14:49,518 --> 01:14:51,769
If we are talking only about power,

1069
01:14:51,770 --> 01:14:54,315
it may surpass even that
of the Ten Commandments.

1070
01:15:06,202 --> 01:15:07,411
The Time of Ruin.

1071
01:15:08,329 --> 01:15:10,456
This is what Solaad
was talking about.

1072
01:15:11,665 --> 01:15:15,127
We'd better revive the captain
real quick and stop that monster...

1073
01:15:15,586 --> 01:15:16,962
What are you guys...

1074
01:15:18,005 --> 01:15:19,715
You must not pull out that sword.

1075
01:15:20,549 --> 01:15:22,092
He is of the Demon Clan.

1076
01:15:28,349 --> 01:15:31,435
This sinister power and the mark
on his forehead...

1077
01:15:31,769 --> 01:15:35,648
He is a Demon!
A high-ranked one at that!

1078
01:15:36,023 --> 01:15:37,899
Is he really from the Demon Clan?

1079
01:15:37,900 --> 01:15:40,736
A Demon was pretending to be Solaad?

1080
01:15:41,153 --> 01:15:46,074
The Winged Sword is a sacred blade
bestowed upon us by the Great Oshiro,

1081
01:15:46,075 --> 01:15:49,036
he who sealed away
the powerful Demon Clan.

1082
01:15:49,411 --> 01:15:54,833
His body is rejecting the sword
and revealing his true form.

1083
01:15:55,584 --> 01:15:56,585
Everyone!

1084
01:15:56,794 --> 01:16:00,589
This man may be from the Demon Clan,
but he is not a bad person!

1085
01:16:01,882 --> 01:16:05,760
Master Zoria, Meliodas was the one
who saved you yesterday

1086
01:16:05,761 --> 01:16:07,554
from the first of the Demons.

1087
01:16:08,222 --> 01:16:11,392
And he saved our lives today.

1088
01:16:12,226 --> 01:16:13,811
Yes, that is true.

1089
01:16:14,019 --> 01:16:16,605
As Head Warrior,
I cannot thank him enough.

1090
01:16:17,690 --> 01:16:18,816
Master Zoria...

1091
01:16:20,025 --> 01:16:23,529
- But Demon Clans are a different story!
- What?

1092
01:16:24,196 --> 01:16:28,866
For 3,000 years, the Winged Sword has
been passed down so that we can fight

1093
01:16:28,867 --> 01:16:31,704
to protect the Sky Temple
from the Demon Clan.

1094
01:16:31,996 --> 01:16:33,998
That is our law.

1095
01:16:34,206 --> 01:16:37,167
Countless lives have been lost
in these battles.

1096
01:16:37,626 --> 01:16:42,214
We must obey the law.
We can never pull out that sword.

1097
01:16:42,631 --> 01:16:44,633
Do something, Granny!

1098
01:16:45,926 --> 01:16:47,761
Why won't you, Granny?

1099
01:16:48,345 --> 01:16:51,098
Master Zoria, the beast
is headed this way!

1100
01:16:52,725 --> 01:16:54,643
Those who can fight
will head there immediately!

1101
01:16:55,227 --> 01:16:56,437
I will follow suit!

1102
01:16:57,438 --> 01:16:59,565
They won't be able
to stop that monster.

1103
01:17:00,232 --> 01:17:03,569
The desire to protect people
has nothing to do with laws.

1104
01:17:05,446 --> 01:17:09,366
I'm going too! I don't want
any more people to get hurt!

1105
01:17:10,200 --> 01:17:15,789
It's a bit late in the afternoon, but
I still have plenty of power left.

1106
01:17:16,373 --> 01:17:17,499
Let's go, Gowther.

1107
01:17:18,083 --> 01:17:21,337
I wanted to observe this exchange
a bit longer, but...

1108
01:17:22,755 --> 01:17:25,631
I don't know about this Time of Ruin
or Indura or whatever,

1109
01:17:25,632 --> 01:17:28,469
but all I know is that if we
don't go, then we all die.

1110
01:17:29,219 --> 01:17:32,638
Master, Princess,
I leave the captain to you.

1111
01:17:32,639 --> 01:17:34,725
- You can leave him to us!
- Understood!

1112
01:17:35,976 --> 01:17:36,976
Ban!

1113
01:17:39,188 --> 01:17:40,981
Show me that you're a man.

1114
01:17:55,454 --> 01:18:00,250
With this power, I will become
the king of a new Demon Clan!

1115
01:18:02,127 --> 01:18:03,462
This is an Indura?

1116
01:18:04,088 --> 01:18:05,881
There's no way we can win.

1117
01:18:06,256 --> 01:18:08,258
You can leave it to us!

1118
01:18:09,676 --> 01:18:11,261
The Seven Deadly Sins!

1119
01:18:12,429 --> 01:18:15,599
You guys protect the women
and children in the plaza!

1120
01:18:16,600 --> 01:18:18,310
You guys are just irritating.

1121
01:18:18,811 --> 01:18:21,355
You can die alongside
the Celestials!

1122
01:18:28,570 --> 01:18:29,570
Everyone, run!

1123
01:18:29,822 --> 01:18:30,948
No, the plaza!

1124
01:18:45,921 --> 01:18:49,216
Even the Perfect Cube could take
only one hit.

1125
01:18:49,633 --> 01:18:52,636
We can't let it get near the plaza!

1126
01:18:52,928 --> 01:18:54,680
We'll have to hold it off.

1127
01:18:55,389 --> 01:18:58,475
New Spirit Spear Chastiefol.
Second Form.

1128
01:18:59,893 --> 01:19:00,893
Guardian!

1129
01:19:03,772 --> 01:19:05,816
Fillet and Roast!

1130
01:19:18,412 --> 01:19:21,665
You've got some grit. I applaud you.

1131
01:19:22,249 --> 01:19:23,876
You're in the way!

1132
01:19:28,881 --> 01:19:32,009
As thanks for what you did
to our captain,

1133
01:19:34,094 --> 01:19:35,929
I'll beat you to a bloody pulp.

1134
01:19:36,346 --> 01:19:40,058
Master Zoria, the Seven Deadly Sins
are battling the Indura.

1135
01:19:40,267 --> 01:19:41,602
Why have you returned?

1136
01:19:42,102 --> 01:19:45,856
The law says Celestials must not run
from the Demon Clan.

1137
01:19:46,023 --> 01:19:47,316
That's wrong, Father!

1138
01:19:48,484 --> 01:19:49,568
You too...

1139
01:19:49,818 --> 01:19:53,697
You threw aside your pride
as a Celestial and ran!

1140
01:19:54,781 --> 01:19:56,742
I don't deny that I was a coward.

1141
01:19:57,493 --> 01:20:01,413
But we haven't been fighting
just to follow the laws!

1142
01:20:10,297 --> 01:20:12,299
I have paralyzed his sight.

1143
01:20:12,549 --> 01:20:15,010
It will most likely hold
for three minutes.

1144
01:20:15,385 --> 01:20:21,183
Meliodas fought to protect this
village and ended up like this.

1145
01:20:21,892 --> 01:20:24,102
But Meliodas is from the Demon Clan!

1146
01:20:24,770 --> 01:20:28,564
The Seven Deadly Sins came
to the Sky Temple for me,

1147
01:20:28,565 --> 01:20:30,484
no matter how weak
and cowardly I was.

1148
01:20:31,109 --> 01:20:35,781
They're risking their lives
to protect my beloved village.

1149
01:20:35,948 --> 01:20:37,115
I believe in them!

1150
01:20:38,158 --> 01:20:41,078
Furthermore,
this man they all believe in,

1151
01:20:41,370 --> 01:20:43,829
Meliodas, the captain
of the Seven Deadly Sins...

1152
01:20:43,830 --> 01:20:44,830
I believe in him!

1153
01:20:45,457 --> 01:20:47,834
Even if he's from the Demon Clan.

1154
01:20:48,085 --> 01:20:50,212
Even if it means turning my back
on our laws!

1155
01:20:50,879 --> 01:20:54,299
I... want to protect the Sky Temple!

1156
01:21:05,894 --> 01:21:07,271
Ow...

1157
01:21:08,230 --> 01:21:09,230
Meliodas!

1158
01:21:09,231 --> 01:21:10,315
Meliodas!

1159
01:21:12,859 --> 01:21:14,861
It's a pleasure to meet
you, Meliodas.

1160
01:21:15,529 --> 01:21:17,281
So, you're Solaad.

1161
01:21:17,739 --> 01:21:19,741
You're different
from what I've heard.

1162
01:21:21,743 --> 01:21:23,245
You look good!

1163
01:21:25,122 --> 01:21:28,208
Thank you for protecting this
village while I was away!

1164
01:21:28,625 --> 01:21:31,128
Sure. I expect plenty of rewards.

1165
01:21:31,878 --> 01:21:34,256
After we get rid of that beast.

1166
01:21:35,299 --> 01:21:36,299
Meliodas...

1167
01:21:36,633 --> 01:21:39,928
You're going to fight too, right?
With that scary sword.

1168
01:21:41,388 --> 01:21:43,015
- Right!
- Meliodas.

1169
01:21:44,224 --> 01:21:45,517
Thanks, Elizabeth!

1170
01:21:46,685 --> 01:21:47,685
Be careful.

1171
01:21:48,061 --> 01:21:49,646
Just leave it to me!

1172
01:21:59,823 --> 01:22:02,159
Everyone, I need you to listen!

1173
01:22:08,206 --> 01:22:09,207
This is the end.

1174
01:22:15,505 --> 01:22:16,506
Ow...

1175
01:22:16,923 --> 01:22:17,923
Heya, Ban!

1176
01:22:18,759 --> 01:22:20,344
What the hell are...

1177
01:22:20,469 --> 01:22:21,470
Captain?

1178
01:22:21,595 --> 01:22:24,973
What the hell are <i>you </i>doing?
You're getting slaughtered.

1179
01:22:25,098 --> 01:22:26,433
Shut up!

1180
01:22:26,767 --> 01:22:28,143
You're late.

1181
01:22:28,310 --> 01:22:31,521
You got beat,
that's why I'm fighting him.

1182
01:22:33,065 --> 01:22:35,900
You're right. It'd be lame
if I kept getting beaten.

1183
01:22:35,901 --> 01:22:37,402
Okay, it's decided.

1184
01:22:43,408 --> 01:22:46,328
You're pretty confident for a guy
who almost died.

1185
01:22:46,578 --> 01:22:50,290
We've got that beast to deal with,
so I'm finishing you quick.

1186
01:22:55,087 --> 01:22:56,380
Hunter Fest!

1187
01:22:58,590 --> 01:23:01,385
- Get it together!
- Don't be unreasonable!

1188
01:23:01,718 --> 01:23:03,303
This guy's strength...

1189
01:23:03,720 --> 01:23:05,430
We have our limits as well.

1190
01:23:06,556 --> 01:23:07,724
What do we do?

1191
01:23:18,193 --> 01:23:19,444
What the hell is that?

1192
01:23:20,028 --> 01:23:23,573
I figured out the true purpose
of the Winged Sword.

1193
01:23:23,740 --> 01:23:27,119
Guide the injured and the children
to the plaza.

1194
01:23:27,494 --> 01:23:30,872
Those who can move,
go support Solaad!

1195
01:23:31,206 --> 01:23:32,289
I'm scared.

1196
01:23:32,290 --> 01:23:33,749
It'll be okay.

1197
01:23:33,750 --> 01:23:36,545
Solaad and his friends
are really strong!

1198
01:23:37,045 --> 01:23:39,423
I figured it out when
you were stabbed.

1199
01:23:39,923 --> 01:23:43,969
This sword was meant to seal away
powerful Demons.

1200
01:23:44,720 --> 01:23:46,888
And so I will seal the Indura!

1201
01:23:47,347 --> 01:23:50,392
With this Winged Sword
from the Great Oshiro...

1202
01:23:51,101 --> 01:23:53,103
and the power of my Ark!

1203
01:24:23,842 --> 01:24:25,009
Clones...

1204
01:24:25,010 --> 01:24:26,219
You sneaky little...!

1205
01:24:31,099 --> 01:24:33,518
Doesn't matter how many
of you weaklings there are.

1206
01:24:34,060 --> 01:24:35,479
You're all just garbage!

1207
01:24:38,523 --> 01:24:40,984
I'm going to end you!

1208
01:24:42,986 --> 01:24:44,321
Playtime is over.

1209
01:24:46,406 --> 01:24:48,408
This power... It can't be...

1210
01:24:49,284 --> 01:24:52,996
You're... Meliodas the Betrayer!

1211
01:25:04,299 --> 01:25:05,300
<i>He's too strong!</i>

1212
01:25:09,721 --> 01:25:13,266
Damn you... You can all die!

1213
01:25:13,391 --> 01:25:15,393
Death Burn!

1214
01:25:18,355 --> 01:25:21,399
Full Counter!

1215
01:25:29,282 --> 01:25:34,996
I won't die for nothing!
I offer my soul to Indura!

1216
01:25:36,790 --> 01:25:40,877
Crap! I'll have to end it like this!

1217
01:25:56,810 --> 01:25:59,521
No... My Ark wasn't powerful enough?

1218
01:26:15,245 --> 01:26:17,205
Crap! It's headed for the plaza!

1219
01:26:19,624 --> 01:26:20,625
We won't make it!

1220
01:26:25,171 --> 01:26:26,882
Is this to be our doom?

1221
01:26:27,382 --> 01:26:29,216
It's all over!

1222
01:26:29,217 --> 01:26:33,263
Help, Mama!

1223
01:26:54,659 --> 01:26:58,371
Mama!

1224
01:27:00,540 --> 01:27:01,540
Apport!

1225
01:27:36,660 --> 01:27:38,370
Thanks, Mama Hawk!

1226
01:27:40,038 --> 01:27:41,665
We have to finish him now.

1227
01:27:42,332 --> 01:27:44,751
- Ready, Solaad?
- Of course!

1228
01:27:45,168 --> 01:27:46,878
Everyone, let's finish this!

1229
01:27:48,129 --> 01:27:49,422
Give me strength!

1230
01:27:50,006 --> 01:27:51,883
All of our power into one!

1231
01:27:52,384 --> 01:27:54,177
All of our power...

1232
01:27:54,386 --> 01:27:55,512
into one!

1233
01:27:55,804 --> 01:27:57,555
Ark!

1234
01:28:03,228 --> 01:28:05,563
All of our power into one, huh?

1235
01:28:06,648 --> 01:28:08,650
Please let me help too.

1236
01:28:08,775 --> 01:28:09,775
Elizabeth!

1237
01:28:10,443 --> 01:28:11,443
Ark!

1238
01:28:15,782 --> 01:28:16,866
Now, it should...

1239
01:28:17,534 --> 01:28:18,534
This is...

1240
01:28:19,119 --> 01:28:22,414
just like the legend
of the Winged Sword!

1241
01:28:22,664 --> 01:28:24,624
The mural shows how it all began!

1242
01:28:25,000 --> 01:28:28,128
The legend was real!

1243
01:28:30,547 --> 01:28:33,717
The Winged Sword bestowed
upon us by the Great Oshiro...

1244
01:28:34,259 --> 01:28:36,261
gives us the power to seal!

1245
01:28:42,809 --> 01:28:46,771
Go!

1246
01:28:50,275 --> 01:28:52,317
I see it! Before it's sealed away,

1247
01:28:52,318 --> 01:28:55,155
we'll bash it in with the power
of the Seven Deadly Sins!

1248
01:28:55,405 --> 01:28:56,405
Let's go!

1249
01:28:56,489 --> 01:28:58,158
Hunter Fest!

1250
01:29:00,326 --> 01:29:02,662
Banishing Kill!

1251
01:29:03,913 --> 01:29:05,373
Spirit Spear Chastiefol.

1252
01:29:06,458 --> 01:29:07,584
Fourth Form.

1253
01:29:09,252 --> 01:29:10,754
Sunflower!

1254
01:29:17,719 --> 01:29:20,388
Rush Rock!

1255
01:29:22,891 --> 01:29:24,809
Blackout Arrow!

1256
01:29:25,769 --> 01:29:27,604
Exterminate Ray!

1257
01:29:30,523 --> 01:29:32,817
Cruel Sun!

1258
01:29:39,199 --> 01:29:41,785
Lostvayne, Sacred Treasure Release!

1259
01:29:52,295 --> 01:29:53,671
Full Counter!

1260
01:30:02,680 --> 01:30:04,474
The Seven Deadly Sins Combo...

1261
01:30:08,561 --> 01:30:10,939
The Seven Deadly Sins!

1262
01:30:25,453 --> 01:30:28,915
Go...!

1263
01:31:00,530 --> 01:31:01,530
Solaad.

1264
01:31:03,074 --> 01:31:04,784
We did it, Father.

1265
01:31:05,785 --> 01:31:09,455
We Celestials conquered
the Time of Ruin!

1266
01:31:26,556 --> 01:31:28,057
You did it, Solaad!

1267
01:31:28,683 --> 01:31:30,351
Yes, thanks to you!

1268
01:31:30,685 --> 01:31:32,020
Meliodas!

1269
01:31:33,479 --> 01:31:34,856
Solaad!

1270
01:31:58,379 --> 01:32:02,550
Thank you all for
saving this village.

1271
01:32:02,884 --> 01:32:04,552
We didn't do much.

1272
01:32:04,761 --> 01:32:07,430
You should be thanking Solaad.

1273
01:32:08,014 --> 01:32:09,014
Oh, no.

1274
01:32:09,140 --> 01:32:11,935
All I did was go in search
of the Great Oshiro.

1275
01:32:12,352 --> 01:32:17,065
But it's because of your courage
that we met.

1276
01:32:18,858 --> 01:32:21,778
While we were too preoccupied
with fate and laws

1277
01:32:21,903 --> 01:32:24,530
and forgot what was truly important,

1278
01:32:24,781 --> 01:32:29,535
you went in search of ways
to protect our village.

1279
01:32:30,286 --> 01:32:33,748
Thanks to that, he met you,
the Seven Deadly sins,

1280
01:32:33,873 --> 01:32:37,335
and succeeded in protecting
this Sky Temple.

1281
01:32:38,127 --> 01:32:40,755
I had thought you
were still a child,

1282
01:32:40,922 --> 01:32:44,676
but you had grown strong
before I even realized.

1283
01:32:46,219 --> 01:32:48,513
Your mother would be proud.

1284
01:32:51,266 --> 01:32:53,977
But what a surprise.

1285
01:32:54,227 --> 01:32:59,147
To think there was another creature
who could stand up to such a beast,

1286
01:32:59,148 --> 01:33:00,858
aside from the Great Oshiro.

1287
01:33:01,609 --> 01:33:06,197
We're preparing for a feast tonight,
so I want you all to relax until then.

1288
01:33:06,906 --> 01:33:08,908
All right,
we're going to party tonight!

1289
01:33:09,033 --> 01:33:12,327
I get to eat food scraps again!

1290
01:33:12,328 --> 01:33:14,205
We don't have time for
that, Captain.

1291
01:33:14,330 --> 01:33:16,874
Tomorrow is the birthday
of the King of Liones.

1292
01:33:17,542 --> 01:33:20,503
And you're the chef
of the birthday feast.

1293
01:33:20,628 --> 01:33:23,840
Oh, right! That's why we were
looking for the sky fish.

1294
01:33:24,299 --> 01:33:25,465
If you want sky fish,

1295
01:33:25,466 --> 01:33:28,970
a ton of them are just floating around
after getting knocked out in the battle.

1296
01:33:29,262 --> 01:33:30,262
Here's one.

1297
01:33:31,306 --> 01:33:32,598
Got it!

1298
01:33:33,057 --> 01:33:34,142
Go, me!

1299
01:33:42,942 --> 01:33:44,902
See you, Solaad!

1300
01:33:45,069 --> 01:33:47,029
Take care, everyone!

1301
01:33:47,030 --> 01:33:49,489
Adios, Granny!

1302
01:33:49,490 --> 01:33:51,951
Have a safe trip!

1303
01:33:52,243 --> 01:33:53,786
Thank you for everything!

1304
01:34:11,137 --> 01:34:14,182
Hey, Merlin.
What was the Great Oshiro anyway?

1305
01:34:15,099 --> 01:34:19,103
It's most likely a name
the Celestials came up with.

1306
01:34:20,063 --> 01:34:22,065
But there are hints therein.

1307
01:34:22,732 --> 01:34:27,820
It seems there was once a huge
creature that shined bright and white.

1308
01:34:28,446 --> 01:34:31,532
It is said the creature possessed
darkness that even the Demon Clan feared,

1309
01:34:31,657 --> 01:34:34,660
as well as light that even
the Goddess Clan revered.

1310
01:34:35,912 --> 01:34:38,623
The people called this creature...

1311
01:34:39,624 --> 01:34:41,125
the Mother of Chaos.

1312
01:38:33,190 --> 01:38:35,067
Sorry to make you wait, Bartra.

1313
01:38:35,234 --> 01:38:38,821
Here's the main dish - sky fish pie,
a Meliodas special!

1314
01:38:40,114 --> 01:38:41,407
It looks delicious!

1315
01:38:48,956 --> 01:38:52,125
Father! Are you all right? Father!

1316
01:38:52,126 --> 01:38:53,711
What a mess.

1317
01:38:53,878 --> 01:38:57,798
I, Captain Leftovers,
will take care of it.

1318
01:39:01,052 --> 01:39:03,220
What the heck is this!